\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8942813\charrsid11886030  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8942813\charrsid11886030  }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 We didn't buy a lot of fruit did we, only bananas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No, We had it give to us and - and if there was - plenty, well somebody'd give father a - apples or - when he went out on his rounds yo
u know or he'd buy 'em for low price you know. Sometimes you'd buy 'em for about a shilling a bushel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you use any tinned or dried vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 You kept livestock on the farm, but did you keep any chickens or livestock just more or less for the family use?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - the only thing - Edie used to keep rabbits when she was a girl didn't she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes, when she was very young, but we used to have chickens down the farm, didn't we.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Y-s. Yes, well we very often had chickens or duck, anything what was going, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Ducks, yes, and turkeys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 And who looked after these chickens and things?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well, my sister, she was the chief one, but the boy what - worked for us and - and ourselves, well - every
 - everybody helped who was capable of helping
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 It was just part of the general running of the farm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 That's it, yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How many times a week did you eat meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Oh - every day I should think wouldn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you ever get any extra meat from poaching, but you had your own land?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Yes. Well - yes, we had - yes, well we had - quite a few rabbits, especially - when - I got old enough to use a gun. And - then we - invariable got a - a - a rabbit han}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4076330\charrsid11886030 g}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 ing up, you know. So if they wanted to make a pie or - or cook it any other way - and me sister was a good hand at cooking a rabbit.
