\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did all the family sit at the table together for meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. Yes, 'cos we had regular times, there was no - breakfast }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4076330\charrsid11886030 at about}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  eight, dinner at one, tea at five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you always have the same places at table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 More or less, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How was the meal served? Did your mother put it on the plates at the stove or would she put it in dishes and bring it to the table?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Oh all put on the
 table. The potatoes, the greens, they were in vegetable dishes. The joint was there, father used to carve it, and mother or anybody else served the vegetables and - we all sat round - and father used to carve according to the size of us you know. Get abo
ut as much as he thought we could manage.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 We didn't - we didn't serve up from saucepans did we? Never served up like from saucepans?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 What order were you served in, was there any special order?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Where did the younger brothers and sisters sit before they were old enough to feed themselves, or old enough to sit at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well we had a high chair or two. With a platform in front. And one a year old would probably sit there 'til }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3352424\charrsid11886030 that one}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  was capable of using a spoon, you know, nearer two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Who would feed them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Oh, anybody handy. You know, what sat next to 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 About how old were they when they were able to join the family at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4076330\charrsid11886030 Well, as soon as they could - I should say - any time after two Doll, wouldn't you?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How about the servant girl you used to have, did they used to eat with you or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. Yes. Yes, everybody who worked in the house they had a meal with us. And they had the same food too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 What sort of person was your mother, was she an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Well - she wasn't a talkative woman, she was - quite, but she very often - chat with us - you know - when there wasn't too many about like, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 She'd have her hands full.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 She did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 If you had any worries could you share them with her or not?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Well - I don't remember - I remember boy giving me a hiding at school, I come and complained about that - and mother said, well you shouldn't fight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 But at least you felt like telling her about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. Oh yes, we - if there was any little thing went wrong - there was no inhibitions at all, not then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Would you say she was an affectionate woman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes, I should. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Could you share your worries with your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Well he was a very affectionate man too. Children, well they - he'd take us anywhere where he was going, take us down to Goldhangar to have a bathe and - take us to Colchester market, on a Saturday. Every now and again. About once a month.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 So he wasn't one of these stiff Victorian figures?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Oh no, no, not at all, no. No, he was kindly. He was a kindly man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - just ordinary, I mean we never - there was no bad language or - we were supposed to be truthful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did your parents bring you up to behave towards your brothers and sisters in certain ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well, we weren't supposed to quarrel I mean we got corrected for that. Boys, well we used to fight occasionally but - not i
ndoors. That used to happen out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did your parents say you should hit back or not if another child hurt you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - I just told you when she - I - I - I got the worst of it and she said, well you shouldn't fight, that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 She didn't tell you to go and give him a good hiding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 What kind of people do you think your parents hoped you would grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well I don't know how - I haven't got much idea of that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 What kind of things did they consider important in life, you say they considered truthfulness very important, was there }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8942813\charrsid11886030 anything}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  else that they emphasized particularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well they - they sometimes said, quoted the Bible.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 If we had a birthday. I think it was father used to say that it
 was always better to give than to receive, that was one of the texts on our birthday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 When grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 What, in ordinary conversation? Yes, yes. Yes. It don't matter who was here, I mean if we got anything to say we could say it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 If you did something your parents disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Well - I never remember father hitting me only once. And I don't know what that was for. I wasn't very old. And - I - I know I left - got - litt
le short knickers on and - he got a twiggy stick and he hit the calves of my legs just round the back of the house here. But what I done I can't say, not now. But that was only time I remember him hitting me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Would your mother chastise you at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 We were sent to bed early. Yes, there was that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Y-s, that was the chief punishment wasn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Would you say you received the ideas you had about how to behave from both your parents, or did one play a more important part?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No, there weren't no difference was there much. No. They - both of 'em - tell us off it we done anything or - silly or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 When you had a birthday would it be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Not much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Would you get any presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No. Money weren't too - plentiful.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Would you have anything special to eat or any guests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 What did you go with your mother and father on Christmas Day? What would happen Christmas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - if we had the opportunity - we generally used to go
 rabbiting, we - reckon we got about twelve or thirteen, so we could set a - a - a - set nets in the ditches you see. Well we'd go rabbiting then. Get out the way. We didn't go to church, did we?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Not on - do you mean Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No. We didn't have a service did we?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well we - I - I mean the - the non-conformist church, we never went to that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No, they didn't have a service I don't think at Christmas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No, I didn't know they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Would you have a Christmas party in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 What sort of games would you play or what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Oh, all kinds of games, have a - my sisters were good at that. Oh, I can't think of them now but when we were small - there was - called hunt the thimble. And the slipper. And - when we got older we used to play consequences didn't we. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 And they could play the piano, we used to stand round the piano and sing. Didn't we. Both sisters could play the piano.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. Yes, they could play hymns. So we could sing - Sankey's hymns and - and - other - songs as well, what we learnt at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you have any other musical instruments in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Only a piano did we, or violin, somebody started a violin.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes, but they never carried on with it did they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No, they didn't, that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8942813\charrsid11886030 was}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  Alan.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8942813\charrsid11886030 Yes}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4076330\charrsid11886030 No I don't think we did, did we, have any other musical instrument.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Could any of the boys play the piano, or just the girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No, the boys weren't - weren't musical were they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No, the girls were not really, not very, only Bessie.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 She could sing couldn't she and play.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Was there anyone else who sang?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No, I don't think - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did your parents play any indoor games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No, they didn't seem to play with us much, I think we had the older brothers and sisters,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 I don't think father played with us much do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No. He played cricket outdoors. But he wouldn't play football, he wasn't active enough.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How about cards or dominoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Oh yes, he'd play cards a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Oh yes. Yes. We had a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8942813\charrsid11886030 pack}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  of cards always didn't we. Play all kinds of games.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Were there any other indoor games you used to have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Oh yes. We had indoor games. Sort of a bagatelle board didn't we.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 And those kind of things. You don't see them now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Then we had - tiddly-winks, do you remember that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Oh yes, oh yes, they had those games for winter nights, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Would your parents join in with those sort of games at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well father played crib. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Were there any books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Can you remember what they were, what sort of books?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - I remember what I read, I read The Coral Island, I read - I was
 given that. And - oh we - we took Poor Jack at school. The schoolmaster, we used to read that. And then - well - indoors here - well had a chance to read - Dickens and - books of that type.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 So you had quite a selection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How about newspapers, did you have a daily paper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. Well when - we had opportunities, the daily paper first come about - 96.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you have anything at all before then, a weekly }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12987859\charrsid11886030 paper}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes, we had a weekly. Had the Essex weekly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 That was the Essex paper was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 But you didn't have a national paper until about '96?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 '96 I think. We had the Second Post then you see. And that used to come about - half past eleven, twelve o'clock. And - the Daily }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4076330\charrsid11886030 M}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 ail was a ha'penny.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Is that the one you had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well I can't remember, I believe father took the East Anglian.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 We had the Daily News didn't we?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 You say you had the second post, did this used to come by post then or what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - the Daily Mail come by - by post - at the start. There was no delivery. No - no newsagents or anything like that. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you only have one post before then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. The early morning one. Yes, when the second post - came you see we got the paper on the same day that was is
sued. Before that - we had the paper a day late.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How about magazines, did you have any magazines at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well, we used to take - the - the Christian World and the Christian Age, and the penny illustrated paper and a - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4076330\charrsid11886030 wasn\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  there a little paper what they took for the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Smaller ones called Grace Darling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes, I think there was a small one, yes. Or little dots or something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. Forgot the name of it now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Do you remember your mother or father reading, did they read much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well father, he - he - he'd read a novel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did they ever read aloud to you or to each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No, they never done much of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Do you remember a funeral in the family before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4076330\charrsid11886030 I remember well - John Wage's funeral. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Was that a relative?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
A farmer. He's a farmer down the road. A neighbour really. Yes, and - after the church service was over, he was a member of the Forresters. And a Mr Wimmal from Tollesbury, he was a very good speaker, and he stood up on so
mething - and - spoke to the people, I should think there was - oh, probably - seventy or eighty people round the graveside, and he - he did speak well, made quite an impression on me.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How old would you be at the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Oh for a guess about eigh
teen. Old enough so I could understand what the man was talking about. But I thought he - that was the - I'd been to funerals before but that was the - that made quite an impression, this man making this - giving this address on the death of a farmer who 
I knew you see. And who he knew well too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did most everyone }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12987859\charrsid11886030 wear}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  black in those days for funerals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Oh yes, that was the custom then all right. Yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Were you taken out visiting neighbours or friends or relatives when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well quite a bit, yes. We had some relations at - Heybridge - and at Witham, and at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Fareham
{\*\xmlclose} near Kelvedon. And Inworth, we got relations - that was a fairly large family you see, me mother's family was, there was twelve of them. And several of 'em lived round - not too far away. Well within driving distance you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 And you would see these fairly often would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well yes, once - oh, why, once a month, six weeks, something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Who would you go with, who would take you or would you go on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No, father used to drive. Mother go with him - and take one or two of the children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 We had a kind of a high trap they used to call it didn't they - call it a high - thing wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Very high to get up wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 It was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Were you taken out shopping at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Well - not much. I remember going Maldon once and - mother buying some clothes for me, but - but we didn't - I don't where - know where she got her - stuff from, do you? No. Yes, go to
 Maldon - father take her into Maldon - when she wanted to go. Sometimes that'd be - perhaps two or three months I should think.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 You say you used to go out with just your father quite a bit, do you remember any other outings with your parents, Bank H
olidays or anything like this, would you go anywhere?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
No, I can't say I do, Bank Holidays weren't very important out in the country, you know. In fact the - the men - on the farm - they never had August Bank Holiday. That was harvest time you see. We
ll they - naturally had Christmas and the - and Boxing Day, but you see then they had some work to do, they'd got to feed the animals and look after 'em you see. But - and of course we didn't go to school on a Bank Holiday, well we found our own - made ou
r own amusements you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you ever go away for a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - in the summer yes. Because we used to have - a fairly long holiday, and - we used to - go and stay with - with the }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3352424\charrsid11886030 relations}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  you see. I'd go to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Fareham{\*\xmlclose} for a week, there was a 
water mill there and a river and a boat. Well that was something - that was a nice change that was you know. Well then - my cousin, he'd come and stay here for a week. And then another one lives at Witham, they were farmers there and - the next brother us
ed to go and stay with them, you see. And then he'd come here, the cousin.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you used to go to Feering on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Oh no. I never forgot - once I went with the carrier. The carrier used to travel from Tollesbury - to Kelvedon. And father drove
 me up to D'Arcy you see, and - with a trunk with some gear - clothes in it you know, clean clothes, and put me on this carrier, well he'd got a horse, well that - well I wouldn't think that could trot no faster than about five miles an hour. And - walkin
g
 most of the time, and stopping at the various houses and - and cottages, you know, they'd come out waving something - well how long that - I think that took about three hours to get from D'Arcy to Kelvedon. Well to Feering rather. Feering - the pit at Fe
e
ring, that's where I got off at. Yes, that used to take - well that was - that was one experience I had of traveling with the carrier, I mean when we went with father well we used to drive from - from here to there, and we had a horse what could trot seve
n or eight miles an hour. Take about half hour or threequarters perhaps, but that - that carrier journey I never forgot that. I thought I never was going to get there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How would you spend your Saturdays in those days, you wouldn't be at school Saturday, what would you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Well - you know, in a village we could always amuse ourselves - find a ball and play with it, used to play various games. And there was - some buildings over the other side of the road there in that - meadow well - we used to pla
y with the bricks, build 'em up and - of course we didn't always do that, we were always thinking of something - and we always had a catapult. Well, we used to hunt for birds - in the hedges you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How about Sundays, were you allowed to play on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Not much. No, no games. No football, cricket or anything like that, those were put away on Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Catapult as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No, no, we'd hide that up. But we - we used to - we used to hide it up too. And - I mean we wouldn't use it about th
e place here, take it out the way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Would you have different clothes to wear on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Oh yes. Yes. Used to, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did your parents attend a place of worship on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 What denomination was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 The Congregational.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How often would they go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Once. At least.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Your father as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you attend with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. Yes. Father bought an old {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}Victoria{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose} what'd hold eight. And he used to drive up to Great Totham chapel, and that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4076330\charrsid11886030 was}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  usually full weren't it Doll?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes, quite a good congregation.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 You had to go to Great Totham from here did you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you go to Sunday school or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Was that at Great Totham or in the village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 That was in the village. Up here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Was that Church of England?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No. Congregational. Yes, a - a small one, a small church, but we didn't have a Minister there did we?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 But a family used to run it. They were connected with us, named Gerson, and they were very good weren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3570294\charrsid11886030  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3352424\charrsid11886030 

\par  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 So you could go to Sunday school here but not to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Sunday school, oh yes. Not to church. That's right. They were very good family, one could play the organ and they were all good singers weren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you have any Sunday school outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Once a year. And we used to join up with Great Totham.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 What was your year of birth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Oh - '85.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Were you born in this village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 In this house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 In this very house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Your father was a farmer before you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
No. He was a miller. This is a - the site of the old mill. And - he took the farm after he - because his father - my grandfather farmed - the farm down the road here. Yes. And when he died - fathe
r took it over you see. But he'd been here as a miller for about five years I should think for a guess.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 So when you started your childhood, by that time your father was farming?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Could you tell us about farming in those days, for example, how many acres did your father have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Sixty-two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 And how many people would he employ on that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - we had a horseman and a stockman, and - usually a lad say from sixteen to twenty, that age, so there was three. }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4076330\charrsid11886030 But we had two employees at the mill. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
And the work in the summer was considerably less in - than in the winter, in the mill. Therefore father could call on them, to help on the farm, with haymaking and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4076330\charrsid11886030 pea picking}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  and - harvesting and so on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 So you could balance your labour out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you start work on the farm with your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - not for a start. I was at - at Paddestow Mill - at - Co}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12987859\charrsid11886030 dham}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  Mill, Shelford, I used to ride a bike to it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How old would you have been when you started your apprenticeship as a miller?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 I was fourteen and a half.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 And had you been going to school up till then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Well - yes, more or less, I left school - in the March, and I was - I was fourteen in the June you see, so I left - I was about - fourteen and nine months when I left school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How long did you stay at the milling trade?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12987859\charrsid11886030 
Well - we had a catastrophe happen here, the sail - first of all the old Cornish bar, that had a hole in it so we couldn't use it, and they're huge things you know and ol
d Cornish bar, about - I don't know, fifteen foot long by about five foot in diameter.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 What are they used for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 To drive the mill when we couldn't - grind with wind you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 You had an }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12987859\charrsid11886030 auxiliary}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  steam power?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes, that's right. Well - t
he - the bar was beyond repair and - then - a little while after, about - eighteen months perhaps - you don't remember do you - then the sails dropped off. All - all four of 'em. And - well then - they all felt sorry for him and they collected - 'cos he'd
 got a large family you see, there's thirteen of us -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Whereabouts did you come in the family, were you the eldest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No, I was about the fourth - fifth, I was the fifth one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How about your brothers and sisters, did any of them stay at the mill or did they all go off and be }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12987859\charrsid11886030 apprenticed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No. Yes they all went out to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 You were telling me about the people collecting for your father, what sort of people helped?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Locals. Yes. And business acquaintances you see, and they collected
 - nearly two hundred pound, and - he installed an oil engine, they were just coming in to the use then. And then we drove the mill with that. In the meantime you see when the mill was out of action, the miller who had been working at the mill, he left. A
nd - well then by the time - the - oil engine was installed I was about seventeen or eighteen. And then I took over then. And worked the mill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 This seems to have been a very neighbourly thing to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 It was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Was this sort of gesture more common in those days do you think, or was it just that your father was a well liked man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Well he was well liked. But - I don't know whether that was very common because - some people - well they're just as likely to be independent, you know, they say, I 
don't want your help, I've got in a muddle and I'll get out of it myself, that kind of spirit you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 It just seems a bit unusual to me, presumably the mill was getting in bad repair if the sails fell off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Oh no, no, not necessarily. I think the sails dropped off - through what they term now as fatigue. They carried the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12987859\charrsid11886030 weight}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
 of the sails you see which was about - well, could have been three to four ton I should think - for as long as that had been built, and when that - fell down, the - the - iron, that was a cast iron - boxes what held the sails and - that was - like - }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12987859\charrsid11886030 crystallized}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 . Yes. That's what it is yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 It was in the wintertime, wasn't it very frosty? Frosty weather.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well I'd forgotten that part Doll.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12987859\charrsid11886030 I thought it was very, very cold and the frost had the effect on it. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
You can't remember -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Well I don't - I don't know whether - I don't know whether - whether I was at home then 'cos I'd - mill wasn't working I went - I went away to work for a little while.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 What about the routine on the farm or in the mill in those days, what sort of hours did you work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Well - when we had a - windmill we used to work as long as the wind blew, you know. Sometimes going late at night, or - early in the morning, if - if w
e'd been short of wind and got a lot of work to do, you see. Then we'd keep on grinding then other people'd - lend a hand, I mean, you get somebody else to help and - and - until we'd got the - sort of we took up the slack you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 And most of the local people had their stuff ground at the mill did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Oh yes - that was - when millers could get a living because no one else got any equipment you see to grind with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 When did local mills start losing trade and when did it become too hard to earn a living at milling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Well, about the time of the internal combustion engine. Then you could buy little - little - little engines about five horsepower, and less some of them, but they could grind and crush oats and do odd jobs, cut up a mangol. C
ow farmers used 'em quite a bit. More than what the - though there wasn't many cow farmers in this area, they were more up the road you know, Ongar way, but still that - that was what - that was the start of it, the internal combustion engine.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 What other things would the mill be used for then other than grinding wheat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Well the chief thing - the - the cow farmers used 'em for was grinding up mangol, they - and they'd have a - a small engine, about one and a half horsepower. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12987859\charrsid11886030 Bentall's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  here made '
em, at Heybridge. And all you got to do is to screw 'em down onto a firm - reasonably firm foundation and - and - where they use say a hundred bushel of mangols a day, well - this thing'd - do it so much easier there and quicker too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 At one time this would all be done by the local miller?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes, the grinding. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
In those days on the farm you had your regular staff, did you ever used to have to hire moving gangs and this sort of thing at harvest time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12987859\charrsid11886030 Well - father didn't, he wasn't - in a big enough way, but - on a larger farm you would have to have - outside help. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 And there was always a gang of men who'd - who'd start - mowing as soon as they could. And they'd take a - as much as what the farmer couldn't do himself. You know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 And in this area would these mowing gangs be mainly local men?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. Locals what were - well they'd be hoeing or haymaking you know and - then when harvest come they'd - they'd walk about with a }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3352424\charrsid11886030 scythe}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  on their shoulder and get a job where they could.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
How about things like gleaning and things like this, I remember mother saying that they used to be taken gleaning as children and then the farmer used to give mother a sack of wheat or something out of the proceeds. Do you remember anything like this, an
y payment in kind, were they fairly common in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
No. I don't think it was but - when you speak of gleaning - in - about - '99 - the gleaning was very prevalent, because all the work was - done with a scythe, but the binder - come into it's o
wn in 1900, and that year - the - we'd had very few storms and the corn stood nicely, and the binders you know, they never left no corn at all. No. On the ground you see. But - that cut gleaning off - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 And this was the year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 1900. Because th
at year we'd - at the mill - I - I wasn't there at the time but the guv'nor told me that he'd - ground - seventy bushes of gleaning corn. And the next year, we - we didn't do about five sacks. 1900. I - I'm - nearly sure that was the year. That cut it off
 - and we used to - we used to grind the wheat what the women collected you see. And we had two claws what went on the - on a spindle. Well the farmers who we ground the corn for - used to have theirs - put }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12987859\charrsid11886030 through}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  a cloth what was sixteen to the inch, in t
he - in the weaving of the cloth - silk so called. Well they were made of silk. So they had a little better quality flour you see. But the working people - we used a number twelve cloth. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 This was how the quality of wheat went was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well 
that took out more of - of the - of the middling - what we called the - now what did we call them - rubbles, at that time. But that was between the wheat and the - between the flour and that was all - in rubbles the brown and the - the - and the finer stu
ff you know. But of course the smaller the holes the better quality of the flour was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How about village life in those days, was there any such thing as bus services or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 You must have been pretty cut off here then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. We were. Well - the two men who worked for father - they used to hire - a pony and cart off the \{BLANK\}
 carrier, and go to Maldon and do a bit of shopping and have a booze up about twice a year. Yes. Old Blythe and - Howson. Yes. Old Sam Friar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
How did you get on for entertainment or recreation and this sort of thing, what was the village year, did you have Bank Holidays or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - they had a local club. And - you - you paid a shilling a month - and when you paid your shill
ing you had a pint of beer. Well then at the end of the year - with what money they'd got - over - they used to have a dinner. Perhaps {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 18}}}six o'clock{\*\xmlclose} at - in the evening, you know. On Whit Monday, that was the day. Well of course they used to have real blow o
ut and - a good many of 'em used to get properly drunk you know. You - you know, at that time, and of course sometimes - amusing things happened. There was - Bill Dean and another - fellow, they were running down the side of the - of the granary there, Do
ll, and that was covered with stinging nettles, well that still is, out at - you know. And both of them went in the middle of these stinging nettles. And they were well and truly }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12987859\charrsid11886030 stung}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  because when they got up they fell in again. That's about all I remember
 about - having a - the - but you see - if they got a - if they'd got a - a man who didn't have very good health they wouldn't have him the next year. If he'd a drawn - if he's drawing on the club. What they wanted was healthy men who didn't draw on it at
 all, that made it a better - for you at the end of the year.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 So it was a sickness club really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Well - they didn't mind a man being ill for a week, but I mean - we had - I remember one who got thrown out, old - Bill - Clarke. Yes. 'Cos he never 
had - well he wasn't a well man. No, he wasn't. And he drew - for about three months one year. Well then they wouldn't have him no more. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Do you remember how much they used to pay a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - I - I can't - actually - be saying soundly but that was - that was about four and sixpence a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 That was a lot of money wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well that was a help.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 What was a farm }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12987859\charrsid11886030 labourer's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  wages round about the turn of the century, say 1900, around this area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - we - we paid the - t
he - the stockman twelve shillings a week and sixpence for Sunday. But the horseman, he got thirteen shillings. And he come on Sunday but he wasn't paid, he was paid thirteen bob. So he got sixpence a week more than the - a stockman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How about their cottage, would that be free?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No. Oh they had to pay the rent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 About how much would rent be then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - about - a shilling a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 The rent wouldn't be too much then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No. Shilling a week and they used to get that harvest time you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How about harvest time, did farmers still brew their own beer or did people still do that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - that had just about dropped out - from what I can remember about - the - when I was about twelve. You see, they'd - a man down 
the road used to brew the beer, a farmer down here - and they used to go down to the job, and the men used to buy - about two }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12987859\charrsid11886030 bushels}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  of malt and a few hops and - and they would delivered down to the - to him and they were brewing the beer. And then they'd have it at home you see - put it in nine gallon barrels what they could handle - fairly easily.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 And this dropped out while you were more or less a schoolboy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes, that did. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Who organised the sick club, was that the local publican?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes, he was - he generally - more or less the secretary of it you see, what kept the finances straight. Well some of 'em did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 And this was open to anyone who was pretty healthy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. They're the ones they preferred.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 What about village cricket clubs or anything like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Yes. Yes. We had - we had a cricket club when I was about sixteen. And - we run that for some time. And - well as we - as the family grew up I - I'd got six brothers you see, well we could all play cricket and ther
e wasn't much difference in us, you know, one goes along, and - well - we were half the team you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 You all played for the village did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. Well we did until they got out, you know, to work. But we were - I was - played for 'em when I was
 - well - I don't know, before I went out to work I think. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
How did you get on for shopping in those days, you couldn't get into Maldon very easily, how would you get on for your clothes and boots, this sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well, you see - father 
kept a horse and trap. Well mother used to go into Maldon about once a month, I should think wouldn't you? I remember that my - but we were taken in you see, if we wanted a suit of clothes - father'd take mother and - one or two of the children what wante
d something, coat or - but the - well we had tallymen come round for the - for the working people. Yes. Yes, they used to come round with a pony and trap.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 They'd sell pretty well anything would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well, in the clothes line, you know, and if they hadn't got it they could order it and - have it delivered the next time they ca-led.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How about foodstuff, meat and groceries and things like this, did the village have its own shops?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No. No, we never had a shop in the village at all. Only a sweet shop. But we had - and still is a grocer - at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12987859\charrsid11886030 Tolleshunt}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
 D'Arcy, and he used to come round on the Tuesday - and deliver the groceries on Friday you see. So a lot of us were served by him. So that - and of course there was butchers enough, I mean, we 
- had - well I remember nine butchers delivering meat in this village, you, nine. But I was older then, I should think, when I was nineteen or twenty so I was old enough to - sort of - sit up and take notice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 What do you think about village life in general, going back to about 1900, in your early teens or schooldays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well I think the people were more sociable then than what they are now, considerably more so. Yes. Would you agree? Of course -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes, I should think so, yes, very helpful most pe
ople weren't they? We were a community on our won really. Yes, home - you see, thirteen of us. That made my sisters older you see than the younger ones, they could do anything couldn't they? Our two elder sisters were very good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 'Cos our mo
ther died early. Yes, she did. What was the year that mother died? Well Jack was born then wasn't he? Jack, the youngest. The youngest boy was born then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. We - we sort of kept a - an open house see so people used to come in and out the house just
 as if it belonged to 'em pretty well. There was a lot of us you see. And - young people, well after the cricket match was over we used - well all - several of 'em used to come - back with us you see. And - well spend a - the rest of the evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 I suppose you had to make your own entertainment then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 What would you do in the evenings? Would you gather round the piano?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes, yes, done that a bit. Yes. Or - I - I remember we had a - about - eight - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 54}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 19}}}six to eight{\*\xmlclose}, and we used to meet -
 in various where they'd got a piano or a harmonium and - and sing perhaps songs. Used to go up - the Crays' and down Mr Gardens, but you - you didn't ever do that did you? Ah that - that dropped out that did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 What sort of part songs, would these be popular ones or would they be folk songs?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well, this one - the - the one I remember best - was a German. Translated the words of it, it was a lovely tune I remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 What was it called?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 I've forget. YES? THAT was a mixed - you know - girls
 and boys you know used to - well we'd spend a couple of hours at it, and then wherever we went they'd make - cup of cocoa, that was the usual drink at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Is there a church in the village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Was this much of a social centre?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
No. The chapel was more. Yes. Was that little chapel up the village and - well invariably had a meeting every week - day - every - one in every week. There was a strongish Band of Hope. And - then there was the Sunday school of about - well, thirty - or 
more children attended the Sunday school wasn't there. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Who used to go to the chapel, was there sort of one lot of people go to the chapel and another lot to the church or did they mix up?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 It was not quite like that, you see, we were non-con
formers they used to call us, not what they call us now, we're just the same, but they - that is the same, non-conformers, but we belonged to the Congregationals - branch. And I think it was a little more open minded than some, but - we got on quite well 
with the vicar. There was one vicar, the Reverend Henderson, he was splendid wasn't he, we were very friendly with him. He liked a game of cards. And he used to come down and play cards with my father didn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 He was most friendly. Of cour
se - that was that time of day, but we had had one or two rectors or vicars but that are not very friendly, but not so now. They don't mix awfully well but - you know, we're quite friendly with them now, and have been for the last twenty years, but in tha
t time of day, you - there seemed to be a division between non-conformists and the Church of England. There seemed to be.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did they organise any outings while you were a child, the Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well, they were very small affairs, we used to take a - the children in a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12987859\charrsid11886030 wagon}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
 down to Goldhangar and there's a - the - tidal waters there you know with a - with a beach, and bathing. And we used to take our food down, and water and - and - fire so as we could make the tea, in a big old - old - cast iron 
saucepan. But I - I reckon as a village we were fortunate because - we never lived under that squire and parson business, you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 You didn't have one here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No. We had no squire, everybody was more or less just - well - not exactly on an equal
, but there wasn't that difference as there was - because when I left here and went to Shelford, that's just what I run up against there and I never see'd it before, you know. And the squire - well, his word was law.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Could you tell us something more about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - the - the squire - in the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}village{\*\xmlclose}
 of {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Shelford{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
, I never had much to do with 'em. But - for the simple reason that - well I was a working boy but he was the treasurer of a - of one of the better societies, I - I believe that was the -
 that was a - a national one rather - I forget the name of 'em, Forresters. That's right. Well he was the Treasurer and the - my guv'nor was - the Secretary, he used to collect the dues. And when he - collected say - two or three pounds, he'd send me up -
 
with this - with the money you see. Well the first time I went - 'course you see I - I went to the front door. And the butler came you see and - and I - of course he asked me what my business was and I told him, and - they asked me - he asked me to come i
n and he took me to the - squire }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12987859\charrsid11886030 Maris's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
 study you see. And he was a very nice old boy he was. But I think that rather surprised the butler that I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12987859\charrsid11886030 should}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
 - come to the front door. Well that's the way I always treat anybody about here you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Round this area it was mainly working farmers was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Yes, they were, yes, there was - there was none of that - sort of - well it is a form snobbishness I expect, you know. Make tradesmen and everybody go to the back door, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How about }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12987859\charrsid11886030 tradesmen}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  in this village, did you have a local snob and anything like that, were there any working craftsmen in the village, a local smith would there be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Oh we had the tradesmen you know, yes, yes. We were well blessed with tradesmen. We had two blacksmiths w
hen I was a boy. And - this - house here was a public house -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Oh I was going to tell you about this -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes, you had two smiths in the village.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes, well - there was - at this - this - public house there was a - the blacksmiths shop, and - a
 wheelwright and carpenters shop, and also a Carpenter}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3352424\charrsid11886030 \rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  shop. Well they used to make - tumbrils and wagons and tramps.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 What sort of shop did you call that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 The carpenter. Well they used to - the carpenters shop was - they used to - build sort of millers carts and tabs, and that sort of thing.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 What's a tab?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 A tab is a - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12987859\charrsid11886030 guv'nor's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  car. Little round thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Like a two wheel one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes, that's right. Well - he employed five or six people, you see. And then - after that we had a retired - old - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12987859\charrsid11886030 Sergeant}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
 out of the - who was a - a saddler in that - he was a saddler in the Army, well he used to do all kinds of repairs in the leather line, and he was a good hand too. Well, he made - two - stool - sort of - what they used to carry over
 the shoulder to carry their books to school, and - their lunch. Big ones, about as long as that, and they lasted for - the rest of them down you know. Yes. I forget what happened }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12987859\charrsid11886030 to}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  'em but he made 'em well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Could you tell us about your schooldays, how old were you when you started school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Oh, about three.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Very early then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. Ah }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12987859\charrsid11886030 well}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  you see there was - children younger than me you see, and the sooner they got rid of us the better. Yes, we started at three. In fact - Rosie, the one 
who wrote that letter, she started at - she went a half a day when she was two and a half. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Was this a local school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes, just up the road. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Was it a Church school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Or a board school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No, that was a - that was a
 board school. And - one lot was - you see, a board school is different to a church school, the parson had got no more right in the school than anybody else. He could go in - like anyone else could, and - providing everything was happy I mean he could tal
k
 to the children and all, give 'em a little address or something like that, though I never knew 'em do it, but I don't remember it. But you see, he'd got a - a board school, who were his boss. They employed him, and they pay 'em. And we got a grant - from
 
the Board of Education in London. Yes. To run the school you see. And the balance was made up by the ratepayers. And the - and the - the payments was based - on the efficiency of the school, the inspector's report. And - we had a young man - from college 
-
 and after he'd been there about three or four years, he got a - the highest report possible. You know, the - inspector had given - first class report. And he stuck and kept there. Until he was - he'd had about twelve years here - and then - he - he got a
 
large school down Frinton. And he never left that, he stopped there for the rest of his life. Well, nice place to live. Got a good house to live in. He'd got sufficient teachers under him - for them to do the work, and he - superintended, but he was a goo
d schoolmaster.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 He was your master was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. He was, all the time I was there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How many teachers were there at the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Only two. And when they talk about overwork - he had fifty-five children in his school in five classes and h
e kept us all going. And there wasn't a boy would - left that school who couldn't read or write, no, no. If he couldn't get them in the - into 'em by fair means he got 'em in by foul. He was a fine user of the cane. He was. But - he was, my - I had a good
 
education that that was possible for him to give on the subjects what he - because I went to the Grammar School, for a little while, but that's a fairly long story, but when I got to - to the Grammar School, Doctor Ryland, he said to me - I don't know whe
r
e to put you Frost, because, he said, what you've been taught - you're good enough for the sixth form. But he said, what you haven't been taught - I shall have to put you in the third, for French and algebra you see. I didn't know nothing about them at al
l.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Which Grammar school was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Maldon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 You had to travel in daily did you for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No, I was a boarder. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 What age were you when you went there then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 About thirteen. An uncle sent - sent the money down to - to mother 
- 'cos a man had paid him - thirty-five pound that he'd owed for about ten years, and he turned his business into a company, and - he didn't - want this money - he didn't know where to put it, you see, so he sent it down to - mother, that was what he said
. Well - that - would pay for a year at Maldon Grammar School as a boarder you see. Well - I was there - about three months, and we had }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12987859\charrsid11886030 diphtheria}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 , and I was one of the boys who got it. Well that was about three weeks before the end of the term. So - they kept us three who got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12987859\charrsid11886030 diphtheria}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
 out the school, and sent all the well boys home you see. Well then before the - the next term opened, they - we were all right, we were convalescent, and we come home, you see. But we weren't convalescents as far as the scho
ol was concerned. So they wouldn't have us in. For another month. Well, that was summertime and there was plenty to do about here, and - and - I never went back. Father'd only paid for one term I take it, you know. So I never went back to school, so I - I
 was - I - I went to the grammar school for about - ten or eleven weeks.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Was it usual for a farmer's son to go to the grammar school then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well, one or two did about here. They - most of 'em come from the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12987859\charrsid11886030 town}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 . The day boys you see. But there wa
s twelve - boarders, and they were the ones who lived a little too far out - because - bicycles were only just coming in then you see. I couldn't have ridden a bicycle - well - they weren't - if I'd have got a puncture I shouldn't have known how to mend i
t, you know or if anything had gone wrong with it. But - the - the boys and - the - the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3352424\charrsid11886030 clergyman\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
 sons from the area - four or five of them - you know, attended grammar school. They were the ones who were boarders you see. What lived a distance away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
I wondered whether it was a general thing just to broaden your education or whether there'd been some idea of you going on to something else where you needed the education. Was there any idea of you doing any other sort of occupation if you'd stayed at th
e grammar school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No, there wasn't much of that, that was just a - a - a decent education for a - for a middle class boy, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How about the working people in the village, what age would they leave school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - thirteen. But some of 'em stayed to fourteen - fourteen you see. But that was only the odd one or two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Do you remember how old you were Doll when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Fourteen. On the very day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 I wondered if there was much absenteeism and leaving early to help in the fields, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12987859\charrsid11886030 pea picking}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  and this sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - there - as we were school board you see we - the schoolboard fixed the rules. Well we used to have a month for }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12987859\charrsid11886030 pea picking}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 . And a month for picking blackberries. Yes. That was how we got our holidays in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 They were mostly farmers on the Board, on the school Board weren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 See, no Educational - like there is today was there? You know, there was a Board they called it didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. School Board.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 The School Board. Well my father was on that. And the vicar wasn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 They were mostly farmers. Yes. Weren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. But - yes. Huckle William and Harvey Page.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes, well they were very big farmers weren't they. That was the squire of the village, Mr Page. You passed his house coming here, }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3352424\charrsid11886030 Beckingham}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  Hall. Historical -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Over on the right?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. Yes, well it's rather interesting, very old Hall.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 I remember }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12987859\charrsid11886030 pea picking}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  holidays but I've never heard of the blackberrying holiday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
No. But that was a - there was quite a bit of money earnt - picking blackberries - by the children you know and the - mothers go with 'em you see and keep 'em on the job as well as she could. Some of 'em used to do - very well you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Where would these be sold, in Maldon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Well, we had a - a local man had a van and a pony, and he used to collect 'em and send 'em up London to the Covent - you know, to the market there, I don't know which one but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Were there any more ways of earning money like this, how about mushrooms or anything like this?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No. This is not a mushroom area, no. No, blackberry - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12987859\charrsid11886030 pea pick}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12987859\charrsid11886030 pea picking}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
 was the best. And black berries come - a rather bad second.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did the farmers still have harvest suppers for their workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No, none of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 That had all gone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Even while you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. There wasn't anyone was there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No, I don't remember - harvest suppers. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 The Hall, 
the Beckingham, they had a tenant farmer farmed it you see, well - I remember ever when Mr Blackman farmed it, well he never gave a harvest supper. He wasn't that type was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well I don't - didn't know him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 But the next one, Mr Page wasn't that type was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How about travelers, gypsies or tramps, were there many of those round here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes, there was, too many sometimes. Little Totham Plains you see, there's a large area there, about forty acres, of common land. And of
 course at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12987859\charrsid11886030 pea picking}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  time - well - I remember counting - eighty-four caravans - on there one }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12987859\charrsid11886030 pea picking}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 It's a lot of people isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 It was. Yes, a - some people who kept a grocers shop there they - they made a goodish bit of money - durin
g their lifetime, by serving the - and they used to serve 'em in the smallest quantities you know, a penn'orth of tea and - that business. Well I should think old Joe Garden }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12987859\charrsid11886030 done}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  as well as any tradesman you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes, yes, there was a shop down there wasn't there?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. That was right close to the - to the common you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 And the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12987859\charrsid11886030 gypsies}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  would always come round at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12987859\charrsid11886030 pea picking}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  time would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Was there any other seasonal work for gypsies, was there much potato picking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
No, no. No, that died out, but - then they'd gradually go away to another areas you see. Lot of 'em go down to Cambridge, that was the favourite place - to pick up potatoes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you have many visitors from outside, if there was no regular bus
 service or anything, I mean did you get any people coming round to look at the countryside, was this sort of thing common in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No. No. I don't remember anyone do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No. We used to go out in a horse and trap didn't we?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 To some relations who lived at Kelvedon, that's seven miles off. Was quite an event if we did that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes, that was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Quite an event. But we didn't travel far did we?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No, all our excitement was - a magic lantern once a year, temp
erance you know, up here at the school, we used to entertain the man who came out from Colchester. He came - we had to meet him at - where did we meet him? By train, you know, Mr. Barnet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well I should say Maldon I should think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well anyhow we used to meet him in a - horse and trap. He certainly never got back at night did he, he stayed the night I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes, I should think he must have done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes, well he brought his - magic lantern thing over. Well we were all allowed to go there, th
at was our one treat. And then the other treat was D'Arcy Flower Show once a year, that's all we had, one in the winter and one in the summer. No other treats apart from Sunday school - outing, you know, which would be at a farm, two miles away, where the
y
 used to throw out these - sweet biscuits, you know, all pretty colours, icing on - that's right, icing ones and we had to scramble for those, and then we had races - on the meadow, at Great Totham, this was miles from here, and a very good tea. That was 
our Sunday school outing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 So any journey of over four or five miles would be quite an event?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Oh yes, it would, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 We didn't go did we, we didn't think of going?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No. But as a family we went out more than the - considerably more than 
the average do, I mean father take us to Colchester market, he - he used to go to Colchester market every Saturday. Well in the holiday times, and sometimes - other times he - he'd always take - me or Bert - me next brother you see - well just to get us o
ut the way, he knew we'd be up to mischief with a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12987859\charrsid11886030 catapult}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  or doing something we ought not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 What sort of things would the village lads get up to then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well in the winter we used to go sparrow catching after tea when it was dark.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 With a big n
et. You never see the things now. Bamboo poles and a huge net on the end. And you brought the together. Didn't you? How did you manage it in the dark?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 You'd do this in a barn would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well we could catch 'em round the premises, th
ey were fetched you see principally. Well, we'd go and poke 'em out the holes with a - with a long pole, then hold the net. When they come shooting out the - you know, we'd cut the net, drop it on the ground and - and get the sparrow. The - the biggest re
cord was - I remember was eighty-four. We got - yes, we caught eighty-four one night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Why did you used to catch these sparrows?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 A bit of fun. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 You didn't eat them or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 And the farmers were pleased to see us 'cos they were - pestered with 'em.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did people used to - I've heard a lot about rook pie and this sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Yes. Well - we used to have one - about the tenth of May they used to SHOOT the rookery. Well - I remember Edie - making a pie once with rooks, but we couldn't eat it. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 I've heard a lot about them but never met anyone that's eaten them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well it was my sister then who made it. She was a good cook. But you didn't fancy eating it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No. No. We got a lot of sparrows - and - we just cut 
down the breast and skinned the breast off, you know, threw the other away, and she made a - a suet - pudding with them, in a basin. Now that was very nice that was. That was, that was good, only we never got enough - to justify that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 I hope they were washed before you made the pie.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Oh Ed - Edie see after that. I remember - taking the breasts off - for her, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Were there many rabbits around here in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes, plenty of rabbits.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How about the ordinary farm labourer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes, they knew how to catch a rabbit, most of 'em did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Most of them had permission to do this did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No, they never got permission but they took it without permission. No, the farmers were fools you know, they used to - they wouldn't let 
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3888667\charrsid11886030 anybody catch}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
 a rabbit with a snare and the old rabbits, they eat ten times as much as what they were. Well - but still - you know - that was very unfortunate when we got this }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12987859\charrsid11886030 myxamatosis}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 . For the working people. That was a shame that was. Yes. That was
. Of course when I - production point of view, we gained considerably from it because we got better crops. But that doen the farm worker. Some of 'em were such good hands at it you know. They - they'd get a rabbit or two every week. Yes, well they'd set a
 snare, they come home from - from work you see and then look at it when they went to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
How about food in those days, what was the main difference in the diet then, going back to your boyhood, what sort of things would you have for meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Wel
l - I think that the - the working people, they - they lived on a limited diet you know, bread and cheese and - bread and butter, and the butter wasn't very good at that time you know. That had got a lo-t of salt in it usually to keep it you see. And that
's - used to come to the grocers in barrels you know, weight about a - hundredweight, something like that. So when that - been exposed and - and towards the end of the barrel that got a bit rank as you couldn't mention.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Was this imported butter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 It was, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 So the average worker would live on a pretty monotonous diet would he, mainly bread and cheese?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well that'd depend on his wife a lot, and of course - the size of the family and things like that all had an effect didn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How about yourself, would you have a cooked breakfast in those days? Eggs and bacon or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well we did. But it wasn't general. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 So you think people live better today as regards food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Oh yes, the standard has gone up enormously, yes, in every way. Housing, clothing, eating.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How about the food or housing of the farm worker, did most of them have their own bit of garden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 And a bit of livestock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. Well not much of that. No. No, an odd one might k
eep a pig, who was a little more thrifty than the others, you know, always having too - too many expenses. But it wasn't general. You don't remember - do you remember anybody
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No. I don't, but then -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Old Harbin, he - he always had a - a pig. At home. 'Til he wasn't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 They were very good on the gardens, the - the labouring men were weren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Ah they were.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you have much trouble with people poaching on your land at all, any }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3888667\charrsid11886030 
gypsies}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Not much. No. No. But if they did it they did it so - they weren't caught, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How about any trouble, did you have a policeman live in the village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No. Nearest place was at Tolleshunt D'Arcy. Well we all law abiding people. Never - I never remember - losing anything much you 
know, not - or father, I never heard father complain that somebody had stolen something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No, I don't think we did lose }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3888667\charrsid11886030 much}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 . I can't remember any stealing going on can you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No. No, I think we were, as a village, very law abiding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Sometimes you hear stories about rivalry between villages and this sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3888667\charrsid11886030 No, there was none of that. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3888667\charrsid11886030 There never was, was there, do you think?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well when we were children - we - we never liked the D'Arcy boys, we thought did we?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
They were very cheeky but you know that died down, there was nothing - nothing really. But we thought they were very rowdy you know and boisterous and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well that was a larger village you see, and there'd be -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 A larger village, and they were more - rough I think, in those days, don't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes, they were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 They were rough as boys weren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. They - there wasn't the same civilizing effect - at Tolleshunt D'Arcy as there was here, you know, the - going to S
unday school and going to chapel - and - they had more sort of social things going on - but the church didn't - and the Congregational chapel there didn't carry the same influence I don't think do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well no, perhaps not. But of course they grew out of it, I mean, it was just - but there wasn't any }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3352424\charrsid11886030 jealousy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  or rivalry I don't think at all, do you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 I wonder why they were a bit rougher there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well I think that was that age you see, they've got - not cricket team or - you see, foot
ball teams like they have today. But my father you see was very interested in sport. And he encouraged it in the village.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Who did you used to play cricket against or football?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Oh - well - used to play Great Totham. And that - yes, and Heybridge.
 And D'Arcy when Mr Jackson was there. The schoolmaster. He run a - cricket team. D'Arcy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 He was a good - very good schoolmaster. He was very good. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes, he was a good schoolmaster. And Tiptree, played Tiptree. And Birch, we used to go over to Birch.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 So you had quite a league of people you played against?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes, but that - that wasn't a league, that was just a - game of cricket.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 You say your father was very interested in organising this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - he - what he did was he alw
ays give 'em a chance to play on the - on the meadow you know, with the boys used to play - on the farm, until we got an organised team, then we had to have a larger meadow then, and then me uncle supplied the meadow then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Your uncle was still farming as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Yes, he was living just down - a little farther down the road. The farm adjoined but - he was a larger farmer. And got a meadow beside the road suitable.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 So it'd be a bit of a bumpy outfield at times would it? Or did you keep it just for cricket, the meadow?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Well, we had an area what we rolled and cut - and cut, you know. But the outfield was - well that was grazed but that was a bit rough grass some places. But that wasn't only our players, that was the same for one side as it was for the other you see.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Could you perhaps tell us a bit more about your actual working life, the actual milling, you said you worked according to the wind? How did you go on for pay? Say for example you had a week or so with no wind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well then we'd start the steam engine then you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you have a steam engine while you were away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 This was usual for them all to have a steam engine then was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - with - with a windmill, yes. Some people used to have a - a - what
 they called a portable engine. But that - and they'd drive the mill - with that you see. They'd have a pulley come outside. And - grind with that. Most windmillers, not all - some of 'em - now this one, that sort of - let itself to be driven - by - steam
,
 because the horizontal shaft - come out, and that - and that drove various things like - that drove the oatcracker, we had two oatcrushers, that drove both them, and that also - pulled the sacks up to the top of the mill with a loose belt and we'd pull a
 rope and that'd tighten the belt and drag the sacks up to the top you see. And that was a horizontal shaft, the upright shaft went }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3888667\charrsid11886030 right}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  through the mill right down to the - bottom floor, you see. What the sails were driving. Well we used to disconnect the
 sails - by - taking out - four - four of the cogs. And then the - the - what we call the crown wheel, the one at the top, could turn round - without turning the sails or the gears you see up top. Well - that horizontal shaft - we could drive with the ste
a
m. And then when we had the oil engine we put a larger pulley on it and - and drove it with that. But of course steam - oil power and steam are different. A steam engine'll start slow, and you gradually get it up to the speed. Now, an oil engine, you can'
t
 - that's got no power unless that's got speed. Well we had a fast and loose pulley with that. And we used to slowly put it on - you see, to - as a matter of driving the mill at the right speed, after - the belt had - had got pull on, it wouldn't slip you
 see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How many years did you work as a miller?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 'Til I got married. Then I took a little farm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 What year was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 1913.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Just before the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Was it a farm in the area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes, just down the road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 So there was quite a lot of Frosts in this village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Yes, there was, yes. And still is. Yes. Well - I got another - I bought another farm up the road here and one son lives there, and I live -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Could you tell me about Sunday school outings, did they have one in the summer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 What would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Well, one for the Sunday school, and - then - we used to occasionally have one for the Band of Hope, that was the temperance association. But - the Sunday school was more regular, we had that every
 year, never mind what happened you know. Well - I don't know as I remember - any particular experience about that, beyond the fact that they used to scatter the sweets on the grass you know you'd get your fingers trod on, and after I got about twelve I -
 I wouldn't - scramble for 'em, I stood on the outside and them let get them who wanted 'em, I didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Would that be held locally or would they take you somewhere?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well, great Totham. A - a - a farmer there - who was - interested in the Congregat
ional church, he - he - put up - swings and - well something to amuse us you know. And they had races and - various - sports like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 You mentioned the Band of Hope, were there any other social activities organised by the Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No, I don't
 re - that was the - the - the Sunday school was the - and the temperance society had meetings through the winter, and they was up at the chapel, you know, that was a -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 What did the temperance society do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Oh they'd have - a lecturer come down now and again with a - with a lantern - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5902469\charrsid11886030 slide}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  and give us an address on the - benefits of - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5902469\charrsid11886030 abstinence}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  to it. And sometimes he'd give us a biological lecture, you know, sort of - more about the evil results of -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 The effect on your body and this sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes, that's right. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you belong to the choir at all, did they have a choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
No. No. But we had a very good - schoolmaster who taught us to ding. Yes. And that was - we were above average for the neighbourhood I should imagine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you ever say family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 At home? No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Were you taught to say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Oh yes. Yes. Yes. We always had to say our prayers. But we didn't stay in the wintertime - too long over 'em. With just a nightdress on you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 You told me your parents were great Liberal supporters, was your mother Liberal as well as your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - she wasn't a - a political person, she wasn't - her family and home - that filled her life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Could you tell me the first thing you can remember about politics as a boy, or any incidents at election time or anything like this?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5902469\charrsid11886030 when}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  I was - getting on a bit, about - fifteen, I took the - the names of the people who came to vote. You see?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 It was public then was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Yes. Well - I sat outside the polling booth - and - if I didn't know 'em I asked them their names you see. Well - I really wasn't supposed to do that, but - that was the only way I could find out so - Mr Herbert Ling who was \{BLANK\} and was important p
erson you see, I asked him his name. Well he took it for granted that everyone knew him you see. And he was a bit short with me. And the guv'nor said, well you - you - you ought to have known him. But I - I - I lived a mile and a half as way from - from h
im, I'd never seen him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 What was your idea of taking these names then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 To check }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3352424\charrsid11886030 that}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  the people had voted you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 So you could get them out if they hadn't been?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. Yes. Yes, they'd look at my list and so, oh old so and so }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5902469\charrsid11886030 ain't}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  voted, you know. We'll send a - and that was in the days of horse and carts chiefly - or traps you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 You told me that your father - was this later on, you told me once about putting a yellow flag up on top of the mill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Would your father do this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
No. No. No, father didn't want to offend anybody. But that was us young ones what did that. Because - 'fraid - you - you see - most of the farmers were Tories and - and - we were doing business with 'em you see, and - and father didn't ca
re for it much, but he never stopped us, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 It was a bit of a risky thing to do really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. It was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How old would you have been when you did that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Twenty-one. Yes. But me younger brother, Alan, he was the prime mover in it. He
 was the one who got a flag, I don't know where he got it from. I didn't have much to do with it because I was thinking a bit on father's lines you know, we might do - offend more people than we pleased.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 That would be about the 1906 election wouldn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
1906 - yes. Yes. Mr Flannery against Mr Bethel. And - oh - and then they had another election down at Goldhangar which was a later one - Honorable - I believe it was later - had }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5902469\charrsid11886030 Honorable}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  Scrapp sit up here, and he had been a sitting member. Well
 - I was working for the Liberal party, they paid me to do it, what I was doing, seeing people and talk to 'em, and - at the election I was at a - at a - schoolroom in - Goldhangar, and - when he come out - from the poll - well we called it the polling bo
o
th, temporary you see, when he come out - there was an old labourer there who was very enthusiastic and had a little - bit to drink as well, being election day you see, he - he met him in the court - in the playground you know, and he - he put his hands -
 round his face and - and give him a - a smacking kiss you know. He was rather surprised. But he took it well. Yes. Yes. That was a surprise for Honorable Scrapp.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did your father do any work at election times for the party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well he - he didn't - you can't say he did much, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Was he a party member or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 He was just a supporter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 When your parents were not working how did they spend their leisure time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - in the wintertime I mean we never had much tro
uble in the summertime, there was always - something for us to do anyway, and - and father as well, after the men had gone, the days work was done he'd - sit and read the paper or - somebody come in. That was a - more of a social - time then that it is to
day you know, people sit and watch the television don't they. But they didn't then. They - they'd walk up and - and - well they - sometimes they'd come on business, sometimes they - just come to talk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Just a neighbourly chat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes, that's right. S
ometimes there'd be - two or three, you know. Mr Cowl over the road, and uncle William and - and Uncle Joe and - oh - they were - sort of more friends, but then - business people used to call occasionally you see. And they didn't mind spending a half an h
our or an hour in the summertime, or in the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3352424\charrsid11886030 winter }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 either. After work was over you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 You said your father was a teetotaler so he wouldn't go in the local pub or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No. No. But we always had beer on the place. Yes, and whisky and brandy and what was necessary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Was that for business visitors?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. Principally. Yes. He'd have it - he'd have a glass of beer - with the customer or with the one who's business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Just to be civil more or less?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did your mother have any interests outside the home of was she fully occupied at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well I wouldn't say mother took much interest in outside affairs Doll would you. No, she had her time fully occupied. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did father belong to any clubs at all?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
No. No. There wasn't a - a club in the neighbourhood, not a - club as go - as you mean. There was - the - the club up here what they used to pay - about a - a shilling a month, something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 What sort of club was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 That was a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5902469\charrsid11886030 labourer's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  - working mans club.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 A sickness club wasn't it, sickness club more than anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Where did they meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 At the - local pub.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How about your father and mother, did they belong to any clothing clubs or savings clubs or anything at all like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How about sport, did your father take part in any sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
No, not much. He used to shoot - occasionally. When he was younger, but by the time I can remember - he'd - he did very little of it. He suffered from asthma. He couldn't walk - far. And I should think that was the chief reason why he didn't do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How did you get on with your brothers and sisters, was there anyone of them you felt particularly close to at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5902469\charrsid11886030 Well, Bert - and I done things together, we were - only a year's difference in our ages you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 A-d - of course we were always - had a catapult and - and there was always things to do on a farm, you know, well - the time never hung on our hands.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Who did you play with apart from him, did you play with the neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes, local boys, you know, what we go to school with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Were you allowed to play with anyone you pleased or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Oh - we }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3352424\charrsid11886030 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3352424\charrsid11886030 what,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  pick and choose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well I mean, did your parents say, I don't want you to play with so and so for any reason or anything like that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No, I don't ever remember 'em saying anything like that. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 What sort of games did you play, you said you were quite keen on cricket?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well we were - we were keen on
 cricket after we had a schoolmaster. And he taught us to play cricket. And then that was really the start of cricket in the village as far as - anyone else was concerned you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 It hadn't been played at all up to this time as far as you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
No. It hadn't. But I believe they had had clubs. But that was a long while before, you know, I mean cricket had - had been played - well for a hundred and fifty years or more hasn't it. It is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 But this teacher restarted it in this area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Were you allowed to get dirty when you went out to play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Well, one thing we usually got dirtiest on a Saturday. And that was bath night. And we had clean underclothes and clean clothes and - and we started a fresh for the next we
ek you see. We got dirty all right. A wet Saturday - well - that was - that was hard luck that was. We did get dirty then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 What would happen on a wet Saturday then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well, I mean - dirt sticks to you better when you're wet don't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you belong to any youth organisations at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
No. There was - there was nothing beyond the Band of Hope was there? No, no - but after - when the war was over, we had a - a club. A boys club. Well - I was - I'd - was married and got children then, b
ut we had a - a - that old granary, which was a fairly large - place, as about as long as these two rooms, and the - and a board floor, and that was - well that was dry and - and you could make it }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5902469\charrsid11886030 warm}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  you know, well - Rosie, she had a goodish bit to do with that didn't she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes, they had a committee didn't they, I think they had a committee?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 But she was the one who started it wasn't she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 And my two young brothers, Ted and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5902469\charrsid11886030 Jack}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 , they used to run it didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Don't know what they did, played cards wasn't it mostly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - yes, and I think they - played - ping-pong didn't they? Didn't they have a ping-pong table? Yes, I think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 But they had nothing like this for you when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How about hobbies, did you keep any pets or collect things, collect birds eggs or anything like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - we always had a dog. My sister, she kept a lot - quite a number of rabbits, but I - she gave me one and that died and that 
was the end of my - yes. No, we always had a - animals about you know. Very often - when I was a - at the time you want to know - my uncle had a - a - a we die having the lambs, and he'd give the lambs - to us - and - older girls'd bring 'em up on the bot
t
le. And - then they'd be about here - well - 'til autumn you know. I remember we reared four one year, and - I was about ten, well I - I used to give 'em a little food before I went to school. And when I was stopping down putting the crushed oats in the t
r
ough - there was one who come a-d hit me up behind you know and put me over the trough, you know. I was just about ten I should think, when he done that. And sometimes they got fed and sometimes they didn't, but the boy who was working here - house - well
 
- any job boy - he used to tease it - tease 'm you see, well one - I reckon one - was - masculine you see, and that caught him in the passage behind the house there, and - but there was a table where the girls used to raise flowers on - in pots you know. 
Well he scrambled up onto the table to get out the way of this lamb. 'Cos that intended giving him a - a punch you see. I remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How about things like fishing or walking, or did you have bicycles or anything like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. We had a - we 
had a bicycle with a - a solid tyre about as big as a - a pram tyre, which we could ride for about a half a mile and then want a rest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 It was pretty heavy was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 It was. And we used to ride down to - to Goldhangar in the summertime and stay the
re - for - best part of the day, if that was a good day, we'd have a bathe when the tide was right and - then hang about and - and pick up winkles and - and cockles, and there'd be other boys you know from Goldhangar, and Barry generally used to have a fi
ght with one named Broweter. Nearly every time he did. But - that was a - a good way of spending Saturday.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did people bother about swimming costumes in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well we didn't. No. As - as we got a bit older the girls used to take another dre
ss down. And we got - when we got about - I should think about - thirteen, twelve or thirteen, we - we did wear a bathing costume then, well just knickers like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 You say you took part in the cricket team, there were about a half a dozen of the Frots in
 that eventually, how about football or any other sports?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Well - as I got older, when I was about - twenty-two or three, we started a club here - and we - we did run it for three years, and we joined the League. The - the North Essex League, but they
 were too good for us. It was a country village, we used to play the 'Artworks. And - there's these Artworks and Writtle, and Broomfields and the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Warren{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
. Well we played about - ten or twelve games you know, and I should think I was about - twenty-three, when we started it I should think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 They had a bit too much manpower to choose from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes, well - as we lost so many times, that gradually deteriorated you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you go to a cinema or any theatres or concerts or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - no - we - we did have a - our schoolmaster, he organised a concert. A play. And we done - Cinderella. When I was }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3570294\charrsid11886030 about}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  twelve, and I was - Jemima, I was a playing the ugly girl, you know, and Claire, who was the pretty girl, she was Cinderella. And - a
nd that was a success too. We - we - that was so good - that we played it and got a full house the second night, we had a second night and that wasn't arranged we - the schoolmaster give it out - before the people left that we'd do it again tomorrow night
 and we got a good house then. And we also got enough to buy ourselves some cricket stumps and - and bats, you know, which we wanted. In fact that's what it was done for. But people who went said that was jolly good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 You didn't get a chance to see any professional theatre, or there wasn't any cinema or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did your parents give you any pocket money while you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Oh - we used to have a regular ha'penny. When we was at school, buy a ha'porth of sweets with.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 This was every week was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Every Saturday. You remember getting that don't you Doll? Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 What would you spend this on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well, sweets. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 We had to walk nearly a mile to the shop didn't we? Nearly a mile.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well occasionally we
 used to save up - a - penny and go down to the book and buy some slate pencils, do you remember that? Well these slate pencils were very good, they were far superior to what the - what the school supplied. And - we could get - mm - I - I think that - I -
 I believe they were three a penny. I'm not certain about that. But that - we used to do that about - once or twice a year and that was a mile to walk, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 You didn't }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5902469\charrsid11886030 actually}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  have a sweetshop in the village then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well that was a very indifferent one. That was very - there was no selection.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
How about the home, did any one help your mother look after the house, I don't mean paid help, I mean neighbours or relatives? What would happen when your mother was ill or when she was having another child or something like this, how would your manage?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Well, of course we usually had a - a - a midwife here you see. And - if things went well - she stayed - well she very often stayed the month. That was quite common at that time. And if for any rea
son she'd got another case or - had to leave then we'd get somebody else you see, local. Out the village.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Who would do the cooking and this side of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well you see - I remember - best - what - me older sisters used to do. Edie was about fou
r years older than me, and when I was eight you see she was twelve and she was jolly good. I can't remember - whether she used to actually cook the dinner, but - I don't remember much about that do you Doll?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No, I don't remember that, no. But they did help didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 They did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 You didn't have an aunt or anything like that coming in to help?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Ah well we did. Yes, of course we did. Father's sister. Yes. And - they - she lived with a married sister at Little Totham. Good, I'm glad you r
eminded me of her. Well - she was always on call. If anything happened she'd come up - and stay as long as that was - essential that - as long as she could do some good, you know. Yes, she was - very often in the house, even after - when mother died the -
 
and the girls were older - Aunt Sue - would come up every now and again, and stay for a week or a fortnight. Yes. She was a very - she was very fond of her brother, and she'd do anything - to help him, you know. I don't think - I don't think father ever p
aid her Doll}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3352424\charrsid11886030 ,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  do you? If he did I never saw any money change hands. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you have many relatives living round about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - 'cos mother's family, it was a large family, there was twelve of them. And let's see, there was - uncle Ben and - he l
ived at Kelvedon, or Feering rather, close to it. And - Uncle Reuben lived at Witham. And Uncle William lived down the road. And Uncle Fred lived at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Haverhill{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose}. So we had about - four or five relations within - easy driving distance you know. You could have tea with 'em and spend the evening you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did your parents see them very often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - yes, that - that meant we'd got to get somebody in the house when they went out of it. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 They did come over every so often. Relations.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
 I - I shouldn't think there was - a fortnight went by but what - but of course Uncle William used to come in more often 'cos he lived quite - half a mile away you see, he'd walk up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 And they would usually see each other at their homes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How about friends, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5902469\charrsid11886030 your parents had}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  many friends dropping in and this sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Don't remember many friends do you? We seemed to be a big family you know, we seemed to have our own amusement.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 I don't remember many friends do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No, well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Mainly relatives?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes, mainly relatives, yes, they were. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Well father being on the School Board and - and also - overseer of the Parish, he had people come to see him about - that occasionally, and they were - local people you
 see. Mr Cowl was overseer with him - and - well, on the Parish Council there'd be Mr Page and - and - William Cox, Harry Cowl, the farmer, well - if there was any business cropped up in between the meetings - you know, because they had meeting about once
 in three months, well they'd come to see father you see, he being chairman. So they - there was occasion for them to come to the house every now and again. More than - than on some places you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Were these also your mother's friends or would she have a separate circle of friends from your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No. No. The friends of one were the friends of the other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Your father was overseer of the Parish, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5902469\charrsid11886030 this}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  means seeing people for poor relief and this sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Do you remember anything about that side of his work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No, I don't remember much about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 You wouldn't take much notice as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No. But the actual poor relief was taken away from the overseers, and that was run by the Rural District Council at Ma
ldon. And - but me uncle was the Rural District - councilor, and they'd talk over the - the affairs of the Parish you see, father and him would. One being on the Parish council, the other being on the Rural District.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 This was quite a close knit community with the farmers in the village in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well they kept on good terms. There wasn't much friction.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 When friends were invited }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3352424\charrsid11886030 into }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 the home would they be offered anything to eat and drink or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - it wasn't usual but if they
 happened to come at mealtime they had the same as we had, you know. But we generally - well they - if they come to a meal that was generally tea, you know, they'd - drive over and put the horse in the stable and have tea and sped the evening, and round a
bout nine o'clock - go home.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Would neighbours call in casually without an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well, quite a bit especially as - as they go - children got older.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did your parents ever go out to visit friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - no more than what I've alre
ady said I don't think. It was mostly relations and - and - they were tied a bit with - a continuing family you see for - nearly twenty years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 You say people came to them more than they went to other people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. I - I - I should think so. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
People often tell us that in those days people made their own amusements, what did your parents and friends or parents and relatives used to do in the evening or when they were together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - Uncle Joe, who was - who lived down the road - we -
 we used to - play cribbage - or - or draughts, father - played draughts. But - what we used - I don't remember much about what we used to do, in fact the only thing I remember is a - oh yes, we always had cards, and we used to play donkey and drain the w
ell dry and - they were the favourites when we were young. Yes. Yes. Card - we played -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5902469\charrsid11886030 Is 'drain the well dry' a card game?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 And draughts. Father was rather good on draughts wasn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. Well the parson, he used t
o come in and play 'em now and again didn't he? And Uncle Joe. Well - a draughts - game can be - fairly long you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 And cards, there was all sorts of things with cards wasn't there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How about music, were you a musical family at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Well - I - no, I wouldn't say we were a musical family. But we had a piano. And - they could play - hymns sort of out of Sankey and Moodies, that was the - all the rage when we were children. Of course - 'course we used to - sing these hymns at - up 
at the Sunday school, and then - Sunday nights - after chapel or - if we didn't go to chapel 'cos the weather was rough or something, well we'd - keep playing, three or four of us would stand round and - and sing. And - we could others - well - we were ta
ught at school - various songs, and hymns as well.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Many people divide society into different social classes and groups, in that time before 1918 do you think some people belonged to one group and some to another? How would you have divided the village in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Well about the only time they got divided a little was at an election and they forgot that in about six weeks for a couple of months and - and then - there was some people a little bit snobbish, but they were the exception.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How would you divide the social classes then, what would you say were the different social classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well there wasn't much division, I mean - the Tories got on good enough with the Liberals - you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 I wasn't thinking of divisions so much as social
 life, I mean most people today would say well there's working class, middle class and upper class? Going back before 1918 how would you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5902469\charrsid11886030 describe this}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - in this particular village and Little Totham - the same - we had no upper class, we never h
ad a squire, or - or a rector, we had a - a - a - a vicar whose - income is low compared to other parsons you see. This is a low a church and the income was low. Now Goldhangar had a rector, well - well he was a man who lived in a home - you know - a larg
e
 house and - and he was a - a well -to-do man you know, and he associated with - with people like - well - the lawyers at Maldon or - or - other clergymen who were in his position. The Reverend Graves - was another one who was - well - they were well to d
o. He - he was - his wife - I believe had got money as well as him, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How about your local vicar, who would he mix with socially?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - I can't tell you, but they were generally a - a bit more friendly than the - than the wealthier ones you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Oh they mixed with the farmers quite a bit I think don't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. And the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 But there didn't seem any class distinction in those days, not here. Not round here. Did there? No class distinction much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No. No. No. No, everyone
 used to respect everybody who was in the Parish, the - the working people and - ourselves, about the - the only difference was that we sort of kept - a - a little better standard about going to religious services and things like that, you know. And - did
n't frequent the - local pub. And that's about the only difference there was.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Which class would you say you belonged to yourselves in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well I should say the lower middle class wouldn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes, I should. About that. Well we reckon the farmers were about the middle class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Which other social groups were there in the village before 1918? Was there a class above you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No, hardly. No. No, I thought we were about the same as them. If we ever thought about it at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well the working class, you see, the workmen on the farm, the farm labourers, well, we knew them all didn't we?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 And of course they lived in smaller houses I mean, they didn't entertain at all. But I mean we knew them and there didn't seem any 
distinction really. Distinction.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 I wasn't thinking of distinction in terms of animosity.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 I mean more in style of living.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Mixing with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well not even that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Their income, the sort of things they can afford, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3352424\charrsid11886030 this}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  sort of division.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 And of course mixing as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Was there a class in the village between the farmers and the farm labourers?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 I don't think there were. No there wasn't - was there? There was no business people lived out here did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No business people. It was simply farming, and the farm labourers, wasn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 You had no shopkeepers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 And - and the - the man who kept the Bell, well he got five or six children, and he wasn't mu
ch better off than the working people. No. Scrivener I was thinking of particularly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How about craftsmen living in the village, blacksmiths or saddlers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Ah yes, well we had - we had them. We had - two blacksmiths. And a - and a carpenter, when I
 was - I'm talking when I'm a boy, you know, about 1890's, '95. And he employed a carpenter and a wheelwright, and a blacksmith, and another odd job man, he had about five people working for him up - just up the road there. And they used to do all kinds o
f work, you know, make - make tumbrils and - paint the carts for the - the local farmers, the traps what they used to drive to market with. And line 'em out. They used to do a little fancy work on 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 What sort of social class would you have put him in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - they were much the same as others. They lived in houses about the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 As the farmers you mean or the farm labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 As the farmworkers and labourers, yes. They earnt a few shillings more, about three or four shillings more money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you notice much of a difference in the working class themselves, were some of them thought of as rough and others as respectable?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well there wasn't much of that really was there? There was generally - one or two black sheep in the family
 who'd rather spend the time in the pub than what they'd work. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5902469\charrsid11886030 
But they were the exception and - and - and another thing, if they got stood off in the wintertime, they'd - wasn't over about eighteen or twenty-one you know, they - they'd go and join the militia. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 I remember two or three of 'em doing that. Do you? They used to come back in the village with their red coats on.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 This was to get a few shillings was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - they - they couldn't get a - sometimes - say from about Christmastime 'til Ma
rch was a bad time. You see, you was on a odd day's threshing, and they had a job to - and they wouldn't - get anything off the Parish you know if they were - young and - and no family you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 They wouldn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No. I don't think they got - I don't
 think they'd get it. I don't think that time - the fellows from eighteen to twenty-five, I don't think they get anything off the Parish, they'd say well you can - do as I just said, join the Army.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 But during this Christmas to March period the Parish would give something to the married men would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Yes. They would. But you see the farmers used to keep their married men on. They were very often - well - some of 'em, they lived - on the cottages you see what belonged to the farm. Well they - they 
stayed there. They didn't get rid of the - of the horseman or the s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5902469\charrsid11886030 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 ockman, they were the - important ones.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Do you think farmers would look after their workers better in those days than now or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well they couldn't. The - the money is so much 
more - that - today - and therefore they live better and most of 'em - have had their - their houses improved or - well they - they're better housed today and better fed and better paid. Well, everything is better for 'em, same as it is for most of us.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Do you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from another, were you ever taught to touch your cap to certain people or things like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 What, do you - mean that we didn't associate with the people who we - different religion or something like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Was there any of these sort of divisions in the village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well I - I don't - remember any do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Would you say there was any difference in the social type of say the person who went to chapel or the person who 
went to church, was there any distinction between the two groups at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well, that was very little.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 What would be the difference, the little difference?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well as -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 I don't think there'd be much difference at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 People were friendly with -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 We all lived on pretty good terms with them didn't we?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes, we were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 It wouldn't be a case of the richer people going to church or anything like this and the poorer ones to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No, there wasn't then. We were all poor you see. There didn't seem to be any class distinction really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Who were considered the most important people in the village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - the vicar was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 The vicar or the rector. There's nobody else was there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Well we never thought about who was most important did we? I remember the - the man who farmed Beckingham Hall, well - people - didn't think he was - anything much of him. You know. Well they didn't like him 'cos he wasn't a very nice man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Even though according to the place he lived in he should have been .....?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes, he should have been. And he had the opportunity to be, but he couldn't, it wasn't in him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Your family must have been quite important in the social fabric of the village, your fa
ther and his brother were farmers and you had the mill and they worked on the Parish council and this sort of things, they must have been quite an important element in the village life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes, I'd agree with that. I mean, there was nothing snobbish abo
ut it. But - father if - if anybody was in trouble - there's one thing he'd always got to see to that, you know. And - on - one or two occasions - I - I did know him make a bit of a sacrifice when that cost him the money, you know. Though he wasn't lavish
 'cos he wasn't a - a - a wealthy man. But -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
I get something of this feeling of community when you told me before about them collecting two hundred pounds or near enough when you h-d the trouble with the mill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Who subscribed to that, would that be mainly the local farmers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Well, we never had a list of the subscribers at all. So - who gave the most or the least we've got no idea. And we thought that was very wise of 'em too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Do you know who actually organised it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. Mr Cowl - over the road. Who was the other one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Was he a farmer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. There was two. But Mr Cowl was the chief - he was the chief one, he took the lead.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How about the local teacher, where would he fit in socially?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 We-l he fitted in with the farmers very well didn't he? We were friendly with all the schoolteachers weren't we?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did he live in the village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes, yes. Near the school. The school house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 But our schoolmaster, he - he wasn't a country man. Not in our -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 One wasn't but the other one was wasn't he, one or two were. I forget the names now, Mr Walker was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 You'd remember different ones I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes, you - it's ten years later you see. But - Mr Wesley was a North Countryman a
nd - and - come from Leicester, and - he - he wasn't quite - the - our type like, and that's difficult to say - which way he wasn't, because - he - he was a success as a schoolmaster. But in - I wouldn't call him a good mixer.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 But that was more his personality than any other reason?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. Yes. That was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a particular social class or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 The what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a particular social class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
No. No. No, she'd - her - father was a - well-to-do, more comfortably off you know. Well I'd call him a well-to-do farmer, at that time. But - there was nothing of that about mother at all was there, no pride or - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Was it possible at that time before 1918 to move from one social class to another do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 To move?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 From the working class or labouring class to the middle class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - there was several did, I mean, boys who went to school with me - when they got - out the village, they - they did very well.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Do you remember anyone who did this, who got on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Well - Arthur Chalice, he left the village and went - to work somewhere in London and - and he got in the coal trade, and then I reckon because he'd a pretty good ed
ucation for those days, he - helped run the business for the guv'nor. Well then he married the guv'nor's daughter and - and when the old boy died he had the business, well - when he was - by the time he was fifty he was - he was - well' to - do, you know.
 He was one. Let's see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 And his brother did well didn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Yes, and the brothers did well too. One got a - he was Inspector of the Police in London. But the other brother, he was killed in the 1914/18 war. Joe.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 One did very well, he was - he was a detective wasn't he? One, Clifford was it who was a detective in London wasn't he?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Ernest his name was. Yes, he got up to be a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5902469\charrsid11886030 Superintendent}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Going back to the village before 1918 were there any what you might call outsiders living here then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Do you mean people who retire and come -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes those sort of people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No, we didn't, you see there was no building going on was there, no building much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No. There was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 To house these people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well Cherry Garde
ns - that was occupied by some people name of Townsend, do you remember them? And then Mrs Garner, well they weren't local people, they'd come from - away, somewhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Were these retired people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. But - Townsend they'd got some - youngsters, w
ell schoolchildren. I don't know where they went to school do you? I think they went away to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 They sound like they were not part of the village very much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No, they weren't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 So you'd have one or two even then would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Do you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you have the police around here at all, did you see anything of the police while you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. When they used to walk. Man nam
ed Saunders at - Tolleshunt D'Arcy, he was two miles away. But he just - this used to come under his jurisdiction, we saw him - well - very often. Once or twice a week. He was - he was about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 What did you think of him as a boy?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well, we thought he was rather fierce and strict you know, we were afraid of him. Yes, we kept out of his way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How do you think he treated people on the whole?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - he kept law and order, he was good at that. I don't ever remember him having to - having a case you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Was there much need for his services in a village like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No, I don't - I don't remember him - prosecuting anyone, not in this village. He may have done, but - I don't remember it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Do you remember feeling that your parents had to struggle to make ends meet at all when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well we didn't feel it was a struggle. But we always seemed to be short of money, we never saw any money about but we lived very well.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Being farmers you see I think, rabbits and so on. But - no surplus money around was there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 But there was enough of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes yes we lived well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 When there was someone in the district whom people disapproved of very strongly was there any special way in which they showed it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5902469\charrsid11886030 
Well - only thing I can think of if any - if we didn't like anybody we didn't go near 'em, as boys, you know, but when - we didn't like - Mr Page at Beckingham Hall and we didn't like the old boy who was - sort of - half st
ockman, half foreman about there. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 He's a fierce old boy and - oh, we didn't go near - we never went on the place, you know, we kept away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Some people have told us about a thing called rough music in some areas where if a person was unpopular people w
ould gather round at night and perhaps beat tins and scare them off a bit.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 You don't remember anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No, we never had that. No. No, bad feeling never got to that stage. No. Sometimes neighbours'd quarrel, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 But that's normal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes, that is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 But they seemed to make it up again didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Were you given lessons by one of your parents or anyone else before you started school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 What age did you start school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Three.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 You seem to have started very young, in that essay of your sister's she said she started at two and a half.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Was this the normal sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes, I remember mother - I remember mother saying to her - when you're three you'll go
 regular, now that meant that she'd - she went in the morning you see, but not in the afternoon. But she'd got to - do the two when she was three.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 And you started off going full time did you at three?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well I don't remember going half time, no. B
ut I remember dragging her off to school, with Claire on one side and me on the other, when she objected to going and she was a sturdy one. We used to one have one hand, one the other and - I remember now - going out and into the road and - hang - hanging
 onto her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you have far to go to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
No, only just up the road here. You passed the school - well it's not being used as a school now, it was sold unfortunately. One the right hand side as you come down, you know the - there's a corner, y
es, that was the school. That's the school building, yes. But the - the private house, that was the - the - what did they call it, the playground. And that was fairly big, for the children to go out to play. But then somebody built a house on it now. Well
 they bought it you see. The council must have sold it to them didn't they?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Was it the council?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. The Country council. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How many children were at the school in your day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Eighty-four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 So there was quite a lot for a village of this size really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 What sort of hours did you go to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Oh nine to twelve. And two 'til four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Was the a church school or a board school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 A board school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Was it a mixed school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you come home for your midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 What did you think of school, did you like it or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
I did. I liked school all right, and so did - me older sister, Claire. Well - we were - we weren't too bad at the - at the job you know. And the sc
hoolmaster, he treated us - well I say just slightly favouritism you know, because father was Chairman of the School Board, well that was a - that was a bit of a - help you see. And we - well I got on well with 'em myself.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How many teachers were there for the eighty-four children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Split into two classes were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
There was - there was two - there was a big - what we called a big room and a small room. The small room was for the - smaller children. There was thirty - odd in there,
 and fifty in the - in the large room you see. And we had five standards, one, two, three, four and five, and he kept them all at work. And they talk about schoolteachers being overworked today, when he got fifty or more to keep employed one after the oth
er you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 That needed some organising?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 That did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did the teachers emphasize certain things as important in life, did they emphasize manners and tidiness and non-school things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No, of course the - the - the - the vicar used to come i
n occasionally, but that was occasionally. Once in a couple of months. He - he'd got no privileges there no more than anyone else did you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 But did this teacher emphasize ways of speaking or accents or anything like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 He did. If you dropped and you got the cane. And that was very common round here you know. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 I wondered if he tried to make you talk B.B.C. English sort of thing rather than your country way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No, but dropping or adding aitches was a - was a crime as far as he was concerned and - he stopped that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 But he didn't actually correct your accent, he didn't try to do that at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - you see - people were getting out of that habit and have been }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5902469\charrsid11886030 
haven't}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  they, you know, there ain't many people who drop th
eir h's now is there? They're an exception now. But they were common when I was a boy. And in fact that old aunt - what - I was telling you about - she was a - a prime hand, she - she wasn't satisfied with dropping 'em, she -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 I wondered whether in your boyhood peoples accents were more individual and more local than they are now?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Yes, they were. No doubt about that. Yes, you can't tell the difference now - nothing like so much. You know, even if you - well the boys sometimes they leave the villa
ge, and go to Yorkshire to work, because the wages were better. Because the coalmining you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Would they go up there for farming or what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 For farming. They - the farmers used to advertise for 'em, and they used to live in a - in the farm house
s you see. And could earn about six shillings a week. Well - they were fed and - and - and in most homes they were fed - a jolly sight better than what they were in their own, you know. The - and - and that was - a good help - to what they put up with her
e
. They'd have a few shillings to spend you see. Well, if they could earn - well - the boys about sixteen'd be earning about - seven or eight bob a week. Well the mother'd want most of that you see, to keep 'em. But they were kept - well. And got about six
 shillings balance on their side you see. And then some of them went in the coal mines.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 I didn't realize you had people go up to the North from here in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes, in - they used to - advertise in the - the local paper. I believe - the - if - my memory good as they had a - a - an agent in }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5902469\charrsid11886030 Ipswich}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
. And - you wrote to him if you want a job, and he'd - fix it up, you know. Because to get to Yorkshire - well probably they - advanced them some money. For the railway fare.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Going back to your schooldays, if you did something the teacher disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 What, the schoolteachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How would he punish you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Oh, with a cane. Oh yes he was a free user of the cane. Yes, yes. He was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Would he cane girls as well as boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - I couldn't swear to that in a Court of Law. But he was free enough with it with the boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 For what sort of offences would you get the cane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - copying off someone else at school or - telling a lie, he'd set his face agains
t that, he - you'd got to speak the truth or you got the worst of the deal. That - of course being late for school, you know, you'd get a - a swipe on your hands - for that. He was a cruel devil. He was.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did your parents show an interest in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Well, not much. Father did a bit. Because he was on the School Board. Well - that was the inspector who was the chief - man who used to come down twice a year. Because his salary depended on the - Government grant then. And he - the better re
ports he got the better grants you got.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did the children at the school come from all the different parts of the village all the village children go to the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes, yes, all - all the - surround too within a mile of the school. And after this
 one had been there a little while - then we got 'em from the neighbouring villages. Yes, people who were - wanted the children to have a - a better education - they'd send 'em up here because he was - a - a good schoolmaster and a few realized this you s
e
e. Well the - the schoolmaster, or the schoolmistress, at Little Totham - well, they'd had very little training they - they weren't fully trained or - and they hadn't got much up top anyway you know. And that applied to Goldhangar - but not to D'Arcy, the
y had a good schoolmaster at D'Arcy. But that was a larger school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 So that put their nose out of joint in the other villages a bit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. That is as it - that - yes, when the - the church you know has got a big pull.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 These other ones were church schools were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Yes. So they closed the board school you see. And we got a - a - a reasonable house for the schoolteacher, and a - a fairly large playing ground, well we could play football and cricket in the playground. Grass grew on it, that
 never got worn off. And - and then - after the first war then we got the playing field right next door. Well we got - all the facilities there. I mean, they could have - got the ground to build a larger school. If they'd wanted one. But you see Little To
tham and Goldhangar, Church of England - and Tolleshunt D'Arcy, well I don't know what category they actually come under, but they were connected with the church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did the teachers single out some children for different treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did he? Yes. He did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
There was - there was one boy who was - who didn't develop very well when he was young, he - he was a dunce. And he did punish that boy. Yes. Although that wasn't his fault, at least I don't think so now, haven't - and 
I haven't done for years. Had got two like that. Boy named Colman and a boy named Sharp.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Were there any gangs or groups in the school at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Were there any children who were left out of things at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No. No. No, there was none of that - sending 'em to Coventry business, they didn't know anything about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 And you went on to another school after this didn't you for a while?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Could you tell us about that, that was at Maldon wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 What kind of school was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well that was a grammar school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 It was a boarding school was it? It was boys only was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you used to board there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 I did, yes. There was twelve - boys boarded there, and the remainder come from t
he town or - near enough to get there by walking or - riding a bicycle you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How many boys were there at this school then, was it a big place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No. Small. Thirty-three. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 What sort of hours were there there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Oh - nine 'til about 
- half past twelve I think. Then we used to have - dinner at one, and start again at two I believe, 'til about - half past four. Then we played out 'til about - the boys who were boarders, we - we were free then 'til about half past six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How long were you there at the grammar school exactly?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 One term.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Why was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - three of us had }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5902469\charrsid11886030 diphtheria}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 . And they - closed the school and kept us there. Because that was about a fortnight before the end of the term. And - then before the boys
 went back for next term, we were sufficiently convalescent' to come home. But not with other children. So I - stayed at a farm down at - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5902469\charrsid11886030 Botanic}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  Road about a mile away, and wasn't allowed to come home because the house was full of children you see. And - 
well that's - then by the time I was convalescent - you see, and I could come home - then the school - had been started then. And father never sent me back. Why he didn't do that, I don't know, but I - I reckon that - he paid for one term you see, but - I
 - I should have gone, but - well he didn't do it, that's all I can say about it, why.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did your brothers go to the grammar school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No. No. None of them. They just had an elementary education up here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 What was the idea of your going then, because you were brighter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Well - our schoolmaster, he wanted me to go in for a scholarship. But father wouldn't say yes - to that. So - nothing was done you see. But there was a good scholarship there, two years - schooling. And probably would have bee
n extended if anybody - you know, was - justified in doing it like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you want to go to the boarding school or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Oh I was quite willing, yes, I liked it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did your parents discuss it with you or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No. No. My wishes weren't discussed at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Could you tell us a typical day at the boarding school, especially say compared in food and things like that, that you'd been used to at home, what sort of differences there were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well, we lived just about the same. Yes, the living
 was - quite good - I could always eat what was presented to me, I never - had any trouble that way at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you have much time to yourself at the school, the boarding school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No, not a lot. We - were - we were kept fairly busy you know, we h
ad - we broke school say at half past four, and we played in the school yard, which was fairly - large - well not by today's standards but for those - that time. And then we had - tea and about - half past six as near as I remember - we had a - another ho
urs schooling.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Like the equivalent of homework?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Yes, that's right, what the other boys done at home. Well then after that - we could do what we liked after about - half past eight, but we went to bed about nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Were you allowed out to go out to the town or that when you wanted to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No. No, we wasn't much to go out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Were you allowed home at weekends or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - I don't remember coming home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Were you allowed to wear your own clothes or did you have a uniform?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
No, we wore our own clothes. But we wore - the - we wore black suits, and some of the boys, whose parents could afford it, had a - a striped trousers and Eton - you know, bum freezers we used to call 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did your parents visit you while you were there or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you feel homesick going away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
No, not - I don't remember that. Well Doctor Rawling - he was very - nice. The Head master. To me, and as I was a boarder you see I used to see him in the evening as well as during the day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 And you got on quite well with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did this going to the school change your attitude in any way do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No, I wouldn't say that, I mean - just be at a place three months and then leave it, well that - that - I hadn't ha
rdly, well got started in the school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 It's not long is it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 If you did something the teachers disapproved of in this school what would happen, what were the punishments there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well the - the boys - that was generally - send 'em to
 Coventry if we - I remember one case of it. A boy who stood next to me was asked a question - and the answer was Australia, and he didn't know it. And I whispered it to him you see. And he said - who told you that was? And he said, Frost Sir. Well he sor
t of split on me you see. And the boys wouldn't speak to him for a time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 So you'd enforce your own discipline a bit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes, well I'd never run up against that, you know, not sending a boy to Coventry. Yes, I remember him - well I remember the name 
of the boy, he - his father was a farmer at - at Witham, and - this boy was a boarder you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 What would the teachers do if they disapproved, did they cane or strap or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No, I never got the cane. No. No, there was very little 
punishment, they used to - they'd got to write something out sometimes, but I never dropped in for that so I couldn't tell you what it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did the other children come from similar types of home to your own or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. Better class. Well - better off should I say. Mm. Yes. Generally speaking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 You felt you were one of the poorer ones there did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Well I didn't feel that, no. No, I don't remember feeling like that. Because - I'd had a jolly good schoolmaster here - and - you see, I wa
s on equal terms with 'em and on - Doctor Rawlings said, well I don't know where to put you Frost, he said. He said, for what you've been taught - you - you know you know well that - French and - and one or two other subjects, algebra I think was one of '
em, what I didn't know anything about at all you see. So he - well because he didn't know what else to do with me he put me in the third form.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Were there any gangs or groups in the school at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Any games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 And gangs? Any groups of boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
No, they were all more or less one, you know, the - we used to play at - rugby because there was a gravel garden, we used to pick up a ball up like - I suppose - that'd worn the ball out if we - if we'd have kicked it about on the ground, but I was only
 there for a short time and - and didn't know much about that. I mean I could play ordinary football and - cricket, but - I didn't know anything about rugby, I - I'd got to learn that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How old were you when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Thirteen and a half.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Would you have stayed longer if you'd had the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 You liked it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you attend any part time education after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 What was your first job, what happened when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - I l
eft school about April time, and - then - I was apprenticed to a miller at - in January, the next - the following year. So I had about nine months at home you see. And I stayed there close on two years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 At the mill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. At the mill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 What did you do for the nine months in between?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Oh - generally helped about - on the farm and in - well done anything what was necessary, what I could do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How did you get this job as an apprentice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 I don't know. But I - I expect that there was a
 - a lot of us at home and father was - and mother were glad to see the back of me. 'Cos both of us went - Bert was a year younger and he started work at the same time as I did. I was thirteen and a half but he was twelve and a half. And he boarded out yo
u see. So we - we were both away - from home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 What exactly did you have to do as an apprentice miller, what was your job?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - driving the - working the mill. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5902469\charrsid11886030 
After I'd been there about - three months, then the - the three or four months, then
 the summer started and we had less water down the river, and we done less work, and then at - I could - was capable of - of doing that because it's a very simple - the guv'nor was al - always about you know, to - if I wanted helping he'd come and lend me
 a hand. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 But generally I was - doing most of the work myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 It was a water mill was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Were there many water mills still working then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes, yes, most of 'em were. Yes. Yes, long while ago, seventy years ago or more. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 What sort of hours did you work in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
All of them. I - do you know honestly in the wintertime, six - 'til ten. Yes. That wasn't hard work. Well - in the - after tea work, I done about a quarter of an hour's work in an hour or twenty minutes p
erhaps. But not - the rest of the time I could just sit about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Would this be filling the hopper again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Yes. Just - and - and we used to put the meal into sacks and - and weight it up. That's one thing I can say about my guv'nor, he was an honest miller. He was. He had what was his due and no more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you have any holidays with pay at this place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No. Well - I don't remember having a holiday, not the following - not - I don't remember - I may have done but I don't remember it.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you work Saturdays or Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No, not Sundays. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How about Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Yes. Saturdays. Sometimes, in the summertime - well in the winter too I'd ride me bicycle home. That's about nineteen miles away, but - I used to come home when ever I got the chance.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Do you remember how much you were paid in this apprenticeship?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Yes. One shilling a week. And was kept. And father paid a fifteen pound premium - because they used to pay for apprenticeships then, but that was - bare faced }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5902469\charrsid11886030 robbery}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  that was, I mean - Mr West - never taught me his business you know. No, never said - I never - had anything to do with the books or what profits were or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well of course you were young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Very young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes, but I was - I would
 have kept his books, 'cos I'd had a pretty good education elementary one you know. I used to book all stuff what come in and - and went out. But as for - what anything cost or what profit he made on it - there was none of that at all. Well I mean that wa
sn't what he was being paid to do. A boy out the village could have done what I was doing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you feel that this was a fair wage at the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - I don't reckon I did. I tell you one thing I did there, I - I bought the - a copy of the Factory
 Act, and hung it up in the mill. And the law then was Doll that - that - that - you - you could make seventy hours a week, but after that you were paid overtime. Well - six days - twelve hours a day is seventy-two isn't it? You was doing a twelve hours a
 day for six days a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 What did your boss say about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 He never mentioned it. No. But he never took it down. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 I take it you had some grievance then, if you went to the trouble to get the Factory Acts out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes, well I objected to the long hours, I expect you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you give any of this money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No. No. Shilling a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How did you get on with the other people you worked with, was there just you and your guv'nor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Oh - no, there was a - a man 
- who was the carter, and - sometimes there was a boy who was about thirteen or fourteen there, out the village you see. But - I don't remember much - I remember one boy but he never stayed long. But generally that was - the carter - the guv'nor and mysel
f.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How did you get on with your guv'nor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Oh all right. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you live with him at his house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Yes, I lived in the house. Yes. And one daughter who - who was the schoolteacher, in the local school, girl about twenty-three. Well I got
 on well with her, she was good company and - and - well - we hadn't got a lot in common but - I used to read, I - I - I like - I enjoyed reading, and I did all I could of it you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 You told me you did quite a lot of reading there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 I did. In the wintertime.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 What sort of books did you read mainly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Well, Cassels, they - they - issued - an abridged - issue of the classics, and there was sixty of 'em, for three pence each. And the guv'nor got 'em in the office where we used to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3352424\charrsid11886030 look}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  - th
e stuff, you know, a little office beside the mill. Well I used to get - one out, and read it, but some of 'em were a bit stiff you know, I - great plays and so on I - I'd read some and then put it down again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Was your guv'nor quite interested in literary things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
No, no. No. I can't imagine what made him buy that. They looked as if they'd been put in - in the office on a shelf and that didn't look as if they had been touched.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you like the work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 As much as boys do like work I expect
. All I know is I - the - the mill kept me on the go - fairly well. But the work was - was - pretty stiff - between breakfast and dinner, because that's when customers used to come, and we used to make up - little }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5902469\charrsid11886030 odd lots}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  - to - take away you know. Somebo
dy want a bushel of maize or a bushel of barley meal or a half a bag of bran, well that had got to be weighed up and - and - and taken out. I used to take it out sometimes, and the guv'nor stop at home if he wanted to stay at home, he'd send me out with a
 load you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 You only stayed at this apprenticeship two years, should it have been longer than that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Oh - well you could fix the length, any time you like - any time they like, that was decided by father and - and Mr West, the miller you see. 
They decided that was two years. But generally speaking apprenticeships were longer. But then that was very often in a more skilled trade like - engineering or - with the girls, they generally had three - you had three years Doll did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes, well my sisters did, the older ones, but I think I only had two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Yes, well there was a - a - apprentices shortened the length of the apprenticeship you see. There were plenty of 'em in the carpentering. That was five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Most apprenticeships I have come across have been five years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 And occasionally seven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 But yours was set at the beginning for two years was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. Well really it - the - that wasn't a trade in the ordinary accepted sense of the term. I mean - a carpen
ter - well - a boy starting at fourteen, he'd be learning his trade all the time. Because I mean, he'd make a window one day and a door the next and - and a gate for someone and - he was continually learning his trade. But this - was just a question of - 
putting the corn in the - at the top of the mill and - and - and putting - doing the sacks and winding up in the wintertime, there was no trade attached to it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How about dressing the stones and things like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes, well - I - I - helped do that
, and - and by the time I left I could do it fairly well, you know. A-d - the - the guv'nor generally used to - help, he done about - well he used to - do about two thirds of it, but as - I got the hang of it then the more I done the less he did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Where did you go after your two years apprenticeship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well, I was home for a time then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 About how long?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 I can't tell you, you know -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 You came home about 1901?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 What happened then, you worked around on the farm and the mill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Yes, well - there was generally a little more business in the wintertime, as far as the mill was concerned, and - well then father had - two things happen. The old boiler had got a leak in it, and that was - old and he hadn't got capital to - to ma
ke it good. And the - the - not - I forget which one - happened first, but then the sails dropped off the mill, all four of 'em. Well that put us - that put father out of business more or less - for some time, until we got the engine installed that I told
 you of you know, that other people - well I suppose they felt sorry for him and - collected the money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 What did you do while the mill was out of business?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Oh - we still did a little, and the - on the farm you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 You still stayed at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Yes. I was. YES? WELL, I had one or two or jobs but - the - the engine - was installed in 1904, the oil engine. It's up there on the - beam now I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Were you then milling again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. Well then - I was - in 1904 I was nineteen you see, 
yes, well I was able to - well I knew as much about the oil engine as anybody else would because they were - a quite a modern invention you see. So - and the miller had left and got another job, so that I took over the - the - the mill then, I was a mille
r, and helped on the farm in between times you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 And did that last until you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. That did. And I was twenty-eight when I got married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Which brings us up to 1913 doesn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Were you just working for the - did you get an agreed wage at the time or did you just more or less share the family profit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
No, I did have an agreed wage, father paid me six shillings a week and kept me. Well, the latter part of it, I can't - I forget what I started with, I probably started with less you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 What happened when you got married then, where did you work, what happened with your working life then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - the farm was about a - half a mile down the road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 You took a farm did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. And I was on m
e own then. But the - let's see, the - I can't think what happened about the - 1919 time, the - well that was the war what - messed things up. A bit. And - 1914, how old was I in 1914? I - I was - I was thirty wasn't I? That was after I was married. '85. 
I didn't go to - I wasn't called up. I got exempted. But you want to know something earlier than that doesn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 You left the mill when you got married and you took your own farm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 You went as a tenant farmer in 1913, did you rent the farm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How long did you stay farming after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Oh - all me life. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Would you have preferred any other type of occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Oh no, that's what I wanted to be that was, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 That was your ambition?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 I was de
termined to be a farmer, I - father had asthma - and he couldn't get about, and - I - thought that was the dust from the mill you see. Not knowing any better. But - I thought to myself, well - if I can - get out the dust I'm going to, you know, and I alwa
y
s liked the farm work better than I did the mill work anyway. So I wanted to be a farmer, that was my ambition, when I was - I never wanted to go out and work for other people. I wanted to work on the farm and - and for father, that's what I wanted to do.
 That's what I did do too most of the time. And other people kept saying to father, you ought to - send him out, you know. But I wanted to work for him, and people - well, help him get a living.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How large was this first farm you took in 1913?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How long was I there?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Well I was there a year. Well then - a brother of mine, he wanted to take a farm. For family reasons, the doctors in their wisdom had told him that - his wife - wouldn't have a family if he was still in business, at Bre
ntwood, he was a butcher. Well - a fat lot he knew about it. Well }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3352424\charrsid11886030 when}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
 he wanted to take a farm he said he'd take a - a larger farm if I'd come in with him you see. Well he hired a farm up at Brentwood, about four miles out, and - then - I got another man 
take my farm here you see, and I went up there to live. And stayed there for about - three years. Well, then when father died, you know, we had to have a - there was a lease on the farm and - we had to sort of - change things a bit. I come down here and -
 and I lived at the farmhouse and took the farm over.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 You took over from your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Yes. And then - we got a - the horseman lived in this house. Well - we - got rid of him, that's right, and - me sisters come here to live you see. And the younger brothers. We'd got two still going to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 So you were able to keep the family together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you ever belong to any trade union or professional organization?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Would you say that full time work changed your general attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Oh - I don't think so, no, I was - I - I got on all right with me work you know. We get the social life in the village, we always took an interest in that, you know. The girls especially, you know. What social life there was in the village - they ran.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Some people say that in those days there was a big division between craftsmen and other workers, did you feel that to be true or not?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well not much here. No. We had a - a carpenter and a - and wheelwright, who -
 who was capable of making a - a tumbril. Or a wagon I believe he was. Man named Thorpe, and - of course - a - a blacksmith. That was the only two tradesmen there was here then. We had a retired - Army man, he come - retired here and he was a - a saddler,
 in the - in the Cavalry you see. Well he was very handy, 'cos he - he could mend all kind of leather goods, and make - some of 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 I'd like to ask you about your life at home before you got married, after you left school.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 You continued to live at home for most of the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did starting full time work change your relationship with your parents or your brothers and sisters in any way do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No. No. They - they were quite a - a - a case of necessity you know,
 I - I wanted to stay at home, and - and - well I - I was glad enough - not to go and work for somebody else, that's what I objected to. But most of 'em went out, you know, me brothers and - and - and the sisters, all of - ones, except one who stayed at h
ome.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you spend your Sundays any differently after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No. No, we still went to chapel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you take an interest in politics during this part of your life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - a little. I - I - I took an interest in politics if they
 paid me to do anything. I think I was more interested in the money side of it. But - father was a Liberal you see and they had a - in a - well - I mean people are Conservative in the country naturally. Well they never could get anybody to do anything for
 
'em - well - the Liberal agent you see had - would get me to - visit the - the - the people in the evenings or - any time. And try and persuade for them - persuade 'em to vote for the Liberal, you see. And I remember they used to pay me well for that job.
 You see, father he didn't mind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 So for you it was for cash rather than commitment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Yes, yes, I - I can't say I was very idealistic, but when they paid me fifty shillings for three weeks - you know - well that was a lot of money to me, earning six bob a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How about your spare time, did that carry on much the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Yes. Yes, we started the cricket club here when I was about sixteen. And - we used to play matches round and - neighbourhood, you know. Tiptree and Great Totham, Heybridge
, Goldhangar, if they'd got a club there, or Tolleshunt D'Arcy. Well that was - it didn't want much organizing because there was a - that was the time of bicycles you see, people were getting bicycles then. And we used to ride - to the matches you see. Ne
ver cost us anything.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 What would you do in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Well - in the wintertime - we used to visit backwards and forwards, there always seemed to be somebody in the house 'cos young people draw young people don't they. And we used to play card
s. And - draughts. What other game? Well - I think cards and draughts took the lead, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 You always used to bring your friends home did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well they'd come. There was a family - of - ten lived just up the village. Another family lived ju
st down the road, you see, there was - a lot of young people about. Oh went for two or three years, we run a kind of a - little sing-song business, had about six of us and - and we used to visit each others houses, where they'd got a musical instrument yo
u know. Harmonium or a piano. And we - somebody who got some idea of it, that was the schoolmaster - he'd - train us to - part sing. And - well that - that used to take one evening a week. And that was all right that was we used to enjoy that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you make any new friends at this time or were they people you'd known all your life more or less?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
No. Things don't change much in the country you know. The farmers stay on and on and on don't they. The - the - the - boys who I went to school with, well t
hey stayed at home - they didn't go to another school, they left, that was all the education they had. And that was all was necessary as far as our schoolmaster was concerned, because he - what he did teach us he did teach us. Yes, he was a good schoolmas
ter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 When you went out in the evenings did you have to be home by a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Oh well, father generally liked us in bed about - be home about ten o'clock. But Saturday nights sometimes that'd be half past. But - we - we didn't think that - we didn't want to stop out no longer, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did they expect to know where you were going when you went out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Well - if they didn't know we used to tell 'em. Saturday nights we used - ride into Maldon. And - sometimes if there was something on we'd go
 to it, but generally we just walk up and down the streets and - do a bit of shopping, because the shops were open then 'til about nine o'clock at night. Or later than that. Ten.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 What sort of things might there be on that you'd go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - tha
t'd be either a political meetings in election time or - sometimes they'd - they'd do something in the town hall, you know, sometimes that was free sometimes you had to pay. But I - I - I didn't - I didn't go very often.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How long had you known your wife when you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How old?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How long had you known her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Oh - about twenty years. Because we'd known the family, not her as an individual. I should think I had met her about two years before I - and - and - and I knew her about a year and then we got engaged }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3570294\charrsid11886030 at the end}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  of another year we got married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Where did she come from, was she a local girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - she was - when I was engaged to her she lived at Tiptree. But they were people who moved about quite a bit, they'd lived a
t Ongar, and at Woodger, her father - her father was, and then they took a farm outside Ongar. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5902469\charrsid11886030 
And then - from Ongar he give up the farm and - and come to Tiptree, that's right, they built the Cups Hotel what's there now. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 And - started to run it as a hotel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 And how did you meet your wife then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Ah well, you see, being - Congregationals and teetotallers, and having meetings. Her - my wife's grandmother, they were - keen teetotallers and non-conformers. Well they used to come down here to the meetin
gs you see. At the school or the chapel, wherever we held 'em. And the - the family were a bit musical. Well - one of 'em'd bring a violin and another one'd - bring a - a trumpet thing, what - a cornet. And make a little music and - and - they'd recite pi
eces and - well - generally amuse - a company of audience for about a couple of hours you know, about seven 'til nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you save up any money before getting married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did your parents help you in setting up a home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Could you tell us about the wedding, what sort of wedding it was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Oh, well they were - me wife's family were living at Ongar then. Privately. And - well, of course I was married there, in the Congregational church - chapel. And the Reverend Good all
 was the - minister, and I spend the night - at Brentwood, because me brother Bert was there as a butcher. A-d then - he drove me over to - Ongar, time enough for the - wedding you see. But - the se all come up from here by train you see. But to make sure
 I should be there I went over and - the night before.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you have many guests at your wedding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - I should think about thirty. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How about presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - yes, I - I had several presents. I had a - suite of furniture for the best room. Yes. Me brother-in-law give me that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 That was quite a handsome present?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Ah that was, yes. And - well I don't remember what we had. Various odd things. But that was the most important thing I remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you have a honeymoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you go away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes, went to London. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How long was that for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Five days. I think I was married on the - Monday and I think I come home Friday night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 And you lived at Sawyers Farm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 That was for about a year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 And then you went off to Doddinghurst?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 For how long was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Three years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 That brings us up to about 1917 or thereabouts, was it before the end of the war or after?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 About 1916 I come down here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 And then you were here from then on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. Ever since.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How old was your wife when you married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 She was three years younger than me. She was twenty-five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Was she working when you married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - they were living - in a private h
ouse, but they had a - a - a lady to teach them a dressmaking, and they run a - they run a - a small dressmaking business. But that - that - that wasn't a very determined effort. Because - Mrs Lavender had got a private income, enough to keep them, but sh
e wanted them to have something more to do - so she could keep the girls at home, there was - three of 'em, keep 'em at home and so they could earn enough to keep themselves in this dressmaking business you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 But it didn't matter too much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No, that didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did she have any jobs before that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
No. No, the wife was home, she never went - never went out to business. She used to go into the butchers business occasionally to keep the books, if anybody - one was ill or - having a holiday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Just to help out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. But she never had a regular job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did she work at all after marriage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No. No, she had a full time job.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How many children did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Eight. I was married in the February and Hannah was born in the December.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 That would be December '13.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Could you give me those up until 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Yes, Henry - Percy was the next, he was a year younger. And Joan was about two years younger. And - Paul - and Margaret were - born - January 1919.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 They were twins were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Were your children born at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you have any medical help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Who did you have, did you have a midwife or a doctor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 We had both for the first one. So we did for the others I think. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you do anything to help at the birth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How soon was your wife out of bed after the birth of a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Oh - how - oh not long. I should think - the nurse was there for about a fortnight. But she was a - a most unsatisf
actory person. We got her - from a - a business place what run these nurses and - and let 'em out. And charged us. But this girl we had, she was the limit, and - we got rid of her as soon as ever we could. But we sort of made a rough bargain to have her f
o
r a month you see, but - oh we were so glad to see the back of her. She'd got no - ain't got no sense. She was carrying the baby in her arm like that and we'd got a - a - the bed had got a - a flat - wooden top, you know, you'd seen the type, and she didn
't miss that baby's head - by an inch. And - I was horrified when I saw that, you know. Well we got rid of her as soon as we could, because wife - my wife had got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5902469\charrsid11886030 relations}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  and - and - well - they'd come over, indeed they were about six miles away, one - on
e of 'em come for about a week. Until Nell was able to look after her herself you see. And that was in the wintertime, we weren't very busy outdoors so that - well, when you got the time you can do anything that needs to do don't you.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 What would the relatives do to help, the cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How much did you have to do with your children when they were babies under a year old?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - I sort of generally helped when I was home, you know, I'd got a day}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3570294\charrsid11886030 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 s work to do of course, but if -
 whatever there - Nell wanted me to do I done before I went away to work, you know, there was no law about when I started work. So that after breakfast, well, you know - get the coal in, or anything else she wanted done, she'd say, oh you might do }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3570294\charrsid11886030 this}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 , yo
u might do that, which I used to do. But - as for - actually running the home, well I didn't have anything to do with that. I'm afraid I never - swept the floor or scrubbed one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Would you have bathed the babies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. Yes. Yes, yes, I done that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Would you change their nappies and generally see after them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well, occasionally but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 You didn't object in principle or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Oh no, no. No, no. I mean it made me sick the first time I done it I know that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Would you get up and see to them in the night or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Well, yes, sometimes, yes. Yes, they - we got in the - like this, as they - got a little older we always fetched them out of bed at ten o'clock. When we went to bed ourselves, then - all of 
them, the girls, mother used to do I used to do the boys. It didn't take about five minutes. And then we never had no trouble during the night. They wouldn't call out if they want to do something, you know. Well - and we consistently did that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How did you work the household budget in those days, did you give your wife a particular sum of money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How many rooms were there in the house at Doddinghurst, you were there the longest weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Ah well that was - there was - there was two rooms }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3570294\charrsid11886030 upstairs.}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  But that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3570294\charrsid11886030 was}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
 a small house. Yes. And then there was a - a - a sitting room and a - and a drawing room I expect some people would call it, and the kitchen at the back which was an extension of the house. So we'd got two bedrooms ups
tairs, and the - other one was at the end of the house like this is, you know, you used that for a bedroom in case of necessity, but there was two bedrooms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you have any relatives or lodgers live with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you have any paid help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Who did you have there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 We had - we generally had girls from school, girls about fourteen, thirteen and a half, that age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you have anyone live in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. A girl used to live in. Well - we had one - live in,
 but you see, time went on, by the time - Percy was born up at Doddinghurst. Well when we - when we'd got two - well I can't tell you whether they lived in - or not because we weren't about a mile off the - the village of Blackmore. And - and this girl sh
e didn't live as far off as that, she lived about a half a mile off. She was a good girl she was. I believe they used to ride a bike then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 What were her duties, anything special?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Oh - yes, well the most important thing was to - sort of when she c
ome about nine o'clock - wash up, and sweep up - and - look after the babies, take 'em out for a walk and - always after dinner whatever happened, but sometimes in the morning, you know. If you got nothing better to do put the baby in the pram and send he
r out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 What did you call her, by her }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3570294\charrsid11886030 Christian}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  name?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How would she address you and your wife?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well, yes, she always called me Mr Frost and - and Nell Mrs Frost.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Was the washing done at home or was that sent out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 W
ell, that was mostly done at home I believe. But - later on, as - as the family got bigger then - some of the larger things were sent out you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How about the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3570294\charrsid11886030 children\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  clothes would you always have }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3570294\charrsid11886030 new clothes}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  or secondhand, what sort of position
 were you in at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3352424\charrsid11886030 that}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Well - well we had a certain amount given us I expect, and me wife had been a - a - had some training in dressmaking you see, and we - she'd also got a - a treadle - a German sewing machine called a Pfaff. And she could mak
e all the clothes that a young child'd want, you know, and did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you give regular household tasks to the children to do to help in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. They did. Anything they could do they had the opportunity to do. And - well, Henry, when he was 
eleven - he used to go out and - help me milk the cows,; he'd milk the cow. While I was doing other work, and he'd - and - and he'd make the porridge, and put it on the fire you know - that was a kitchen stove, he'd put it so it didn't burn you know. Let'
s see, what else, well he was a - a good boy, he'd do a bit - he'd - he'd do threequarters of an hours work before he went to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did they have regular jobs or more or less what they felt like doing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No, no, Henry had - he took that on as his regular job that one. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3570294\charrsid11886030 Milking}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
 the cows When that - of course you arrange these things as they come handy don't you, well - sometimes - when - the cow was in calf again that wouldn't give much milk you see, give about a couple of quarts say. Well, he - he'
d go out and milk that in about ten minutes you see. I used to do the harder work but he - he'd nip out and milk the cow, and then go back to see after breakfast you know, and - and set the breakfast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How about the other children, would they have regular jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Well - the - the - the daughter, she weren't very keen on work, she'd do the milling. But Henry and Percy, they were all right, they were no trouble.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 What time did you send your children to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - early. Because - Nell wante
d the place clear of - so that she could get on with her needlework and have a little peace, you know. The younger fry used to go to bed at six. You see, well, somebody asked Henry when he was young you know well what time do you go to bed? He said, when 
the clock is like that. You know, and he stretched his hands out. Six o'clock. This was wintertime you know, when it was dark.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 What were the sleeping arrangements in the house there then, you had one room and one for the children did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No. No. They were - I'd only got two when I come down here. That's quite all right. I've got no objection at all. He wasn't a bit }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3570294\charrsid11886030 bigoted}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  about }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3570294\charrsid11886030 religion}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  you know. Well it was, 'cos it wasn't usual.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Would you say there was much change in your eating habits at this time from your childhood, or was your diet, menu, style of cooking }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3570294\charrsid11886030 much}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  the same in your married home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. Yes, just about the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did your wife make any jam or pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Oh yes. Yes, she was a dab hand at that. Yes. Yes. Everything what was - usable, you know. Well just carried on -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How about the children, were they allowed to talk at the meal table or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How about if they left food uneaten, were they allowed to do this or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 YES? We never pressed
 food on 'em. No. Or - we never made 'em clear up the plate or anything like that. No, no, I always objected to that was a child myself, and - you know, they - we served 'em according to their appetite, if they want some more they could have it. If there 
was - you know, as long as that'd go around like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 When could they leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - generally speaking they sat there about the same time as we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 More or less all leave together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Oh yes, we - we didn't have - get off the chair
s and - and run about the room while we were having a meal. They sat up when we did and they - and they got up when we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Would you allow them to bring a book or anything like this to the table?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No. No, we didn't read at meals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you have regular places at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 When your children were young did you feel that there was a right way and a wrong way of bringing up children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes, I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did your wife and you have the same ideas, did you discuss this at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Yes, very much the same ideas. We were - both brought up - as - non-conformists and - and the Congregational brand you know. Yes, I should - I should think they were very much a like Doll shouldn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Oh yes, you backed each other up which was the principle thing wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Was there anyone you used to talk to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3352424\charrsid11886030 if}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  you were worried about the children, was there anyone you could turn to for advice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Ah yes. We got a - a sister up here who - very often was a help you know. 
Especially - well if anything was wrong, a little illness say, earache. I remember she saved our bacon one day. Because - we got a - a - one of the twins had got earache, and - that was very painful. And she came down, and she said to us, she said, that's
 - this was worse than what that ought to be, that's worse than the ordinary earache. So - I got on me bicycle and - and went and got the doctor who was at Tiptree about three miles away. And he diagnosed a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3570294\charrsid11886030 mastitis}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  - mastitis. Is that the right word? Masto
id, that's the one, mastoid. Well - and this was about - oh - sometime in the afternoon I think, about two or three o'clock time. And he said, I'll go back - and - I'll get a bed for her in a hospital you see. Well, if that wasn't a performance, he got a 
b
ed in - Kings College Hospital, in London. And we got a taxi and - and took her up, because by the time we'd made it - organised it you know this was five o'clock. Or half past in the wintertime. So I went up with her in the taxi. And when we got there no
 one knew anything. And I hung bout in Kings College Hospital 'til quarter to eleven that night before we could find someone to take this child over. And then they put her in the - in the - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3570294\charrsid11886030 
children\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  ward, we'd got her in a little cubicle before, and after
 - the doctors next morning - they diagnosed - some kind of fever, what was that? Some kind of fever, and they sent her to an isolation hospital down Surrey. And of course that was during the depression, and I hadn't - I - we were all very short of money.
 
Well, we never saw this child for nine weeks. But we - if that was a mastoid that didn't - they didn't operate, and that didn't - and that didn't - that didn't burst. But anyway, she was there nine weeks. But we got a - me wife's sister lived in London, a
nd she went down to see her, two or three times. They were better off and - and they were so much nearer you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How about your mother-in-law, did she I've near enough for you to ask her advice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No, not - no, she was too far away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Going ba
ck to your children, could you tell me some of the things you felt you ought to do for them? Well sort of things you felt important, discipline, affection or safety, things like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - me wife was very keen on education. Yes. And - she done - a
ll she could - to get 'em as good an education as possible. And - though - we didn't - have any money - we got 'em - seven out of the eight had a secondary education. Without me playing. They got scholarships and - and later on, you know, the - well - I d
on't know how - well they got to Maldon grammar school. This one with the mastoid, Peg and David. And the three boys went to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Colchester{\*\xmlclose} 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Technical{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}College{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. That was a little bit - later than 1918, that was '28 - to '30 you see. Yes, that is }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3570294\charrsid11886030 isn\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How did you want the children to behave towards you and your wife?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well, I think - we never had any trouble, you know. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Quite a happy family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - they may have had a - a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3570294\charrsid11886030 spank}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  if they were a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3570294\charrsid11886030 nuisance}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  you know, but that was very seldom,
 I can tell you that. They never make trouble.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 When the children were young did you ever both manage to leave them so you could go out together at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No, we never left 'em. If we went out we got somebody else to come in - a grown up person in the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Would this be a friend or a relative you would have come in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Yes. Yes, one of the - one of the girls from here or - if they couldn't come we'd get a woman up the village, a Mrs Wade, she used to come - occasionally. I - I don't - we didn't go out a lot you know. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you let your children join in when grown ups were talking?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Oh yes, there was no inhibitions of that then. If they thought of anything to say they had the opportunity to say it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 What did you bring them up to consider important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well I think that - me wife thought that a - good education was the most important thing. And she done - what she could to get 'em that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you tell them they should hit back or not if another child hurt them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 What's that? No. No, we never - we never encouraged or - any of it indoors either. They'd got to behave themselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Were there any other children you discouraged them from playing with at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No rough children in the village or anything like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
No. No, I allowed - I - I never stopped a boy from coming on the farm, don't remember it once. I'd - I - I'd give 'em one if - if they done anything - silly or wrong you know, like I did me own. I wouldn't - let 'em get up to - 
sort of just wanton mischief you know. No, and I'm on good terms with 'em now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
You say you'd give them a very occasional spank if they deserved it, did you have any other forms of punishment you would use? Did you send them to bed earlier and this sort of thing or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
No. I did - hit a boy across the behind with a thrashing pin. Because he - I'd a new carborundum what we sharp the - the tools with you see. And he was up on the stack, he was a boy about twelve I should think, and he threw it down
 on the ground and broke it in half you see, and I saw him do this. So I give him one or two for that, and I said, don't you come back here no more. Boy Kettley. Well - you know - he didn't like to keep away but he kept away about three Saturdays. And on 
the fourth he crept back again. 'Cos I never see him, I let it go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Would you say your children received the ideas they had about how to behave from both of you or would you say one of you played a more important role than the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well, I should think the one who had - the greatest influence was Edie for a start.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Your sister, yes, our sister, yes. She's a great one on temperance. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3570294\charrsid11886030 
You know, we all had to sign the pledge - when we were about ten or twelve, it was just a card, you signed that you wouldn't have any intoxicating drinks - with God's help you know. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
We've departed a little way from that all the same.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 I haven't kept it I can tell you that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 I don't think many children do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No, but - we have. Doll -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Our generation has - our generation, more or less, because we dislike it so don't we
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 You never touch it do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Not for years and years. In fact the only time now I had a drink was when we go to a wedding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 When your children had a birthday would that be different from other days, did they have any presents or anything like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Not much. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did they have a party or anything like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well, I don't remember. Not much. No. Well we didn't have any money for -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 I wondered if you served your children the same as when you were young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Well there - there - might have been when they were small, you know, we'd put a cake or two on - candle or two on the cake or something like that, but there was nothing much. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Can you remember anything you did with your wife }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3570294\charrsid11886030 and}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  children on Christmas day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Ah well, we - we did have - considerably more - of a fuss made of Christmastime. Because that was a - a kind of a family gathering you see. And - this was the - house he
re was the meeting place for - for the children, always had a party. And - my sister - another sister was a very good hand at organising games. And they used to have a jolly good time, you know, well - she a rare one for pencil and paper, she'd play games
 like consequences and - as they got a bit older you know and hunt the thimble and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 This would be with all their cousins?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you have any musical instruments in the house when you were first married?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well, no, we weren't a very musical family. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How about playing games with the children, did you used to play with them much when they were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - in the wintertime, as they got - oh we always had games indoors, you know, like - cards, yes, we used to play cards. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3570294\charrsid11886030 
Directly they were - could tell a Jack from a Queen we used to play various games like - Beggar me Neighbour and - and - let's see, what other games - yes, Old Maid, that was another one, I was trying to think of that one.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did your wife used to join in with these as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Oh yes. Yes. But - she was a busy woman, and she didn't spend much time - playing cards. And really - you see - they went to }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3570294\charrsid11886030 bed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  early. They were - until I should think they were - eleven or twelve they were in bed about seven 
in the wintertime. And then - mother had a lot of needlework to do 'cos there was several of 'em and - and - she could get on with her needlework when they were in bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you used to read aloud to each other or to the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Oh yes. Yes. I 
used to read - well I think the one that made the great impression on 'em as they got a bit older was Longfellow, I used to read the Tales of - the Tales of Whiteside Inn. They - they quote that now sometimes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you have many books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How about newspapers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. We had a new - a daily.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you belong to a library at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Was there a library near?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No. I don't when the library started in the village. Do you remember Doll?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No. Oh no, but some time ago. Over twenty years ago isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Yes. Yes. It's been going twenty years, but I mean my children are fifty years old now. There was no shortage of - of various books in the house. All - you know, like well Alice in Wonderland and - let's see, what else was there?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3570294\charrsid11886030 Did you take the Children's Newspaper?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No, but we used to have it sent to us. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3570294\charrsid11886030 
Old friend of ours used to send it to us - once a week, the Children's Newspaper. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 And a jolly good newspaper that was too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 I don't think I've heard of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Haven't you? I believe that's still in existence
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No it's not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Ain't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No, no, it's not. But it was - who - who was the editor of that? It wasn't Arthur Bryant was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 I believe it was, I believe I do remember something about it now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
I've forgotten. Arthur Mee. Yes. No, I ain't certain about that. But that was a very nice paper. That reported - the - just the opposite of what the press does. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3570294\charrsid11886030 
If that knew of a good thing or somebody had done a nice turn or - that was in the news - in the Children's Newspaper. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
There was no law suits or divorces or - well - nothing of that at all, nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 It was partly religious wasn't it too? Partly religious.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 It was a way of life, recommended you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
It was. The people who sent this - he was a - he was - what do they call the - the Captain of the - the printing house in the Daily News. That ain't the right word, not the Captain isn't. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3570294\charrsid11886030 
But - he used to send me the New Statesman, and - his wife to send Nell the News - the Children's Newspaper. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
So - newspapers were fairly up to date. You know, you couldn't get anything - much better - in the political world, I mean, I know the New Statesman is a sort of a - a leftish paper but there's a
 lot of information in it. And still is. Though I don't take it now, I take the Listener now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 When you and your wife were not doing your work how did you spend your leisure time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - I played - both football in the winter and cricket in the s
ummer. But - me wife, she never had much time, because - you see, the first boy was born in 1913, by the time - up to 1918 we'd got five.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 She'd have her hands full?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 She did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did she have any interests at all outside the home, did she go out on her own at all? Did she visit anywhere at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
No, well - you see we couldn't do that very much. We - because we were tied by the age of the children you see, you can't - don't cart babies about far do you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you belong to any savings clubs at this time, any boot clubs or sick clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did anyone outside the home help your wife look after the house or family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - sometimes we had a - a girl out the village, you know, girl about fourteen. They'd come to us for 
a year or two and then - get a - when they'd had a bit of training and - and knew which side to put the knife and fork, you know, then they'd get a better job you see. And mostly they come from close so that they could go home at nights to sleep, you know
.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
If your wife was confined to bed how did you manage? For example when the children were born how did you get on for your meals and things then, who looked after the house then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - I remember me sisters used to come down or we had a - a - a 
woman who lived very close and she'd - after - other help had gone she'd come and cook the dinner, and do some of the housework, say from about ten o'clock 'til one or two or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 So you were fortunate in having plenty of relatives living nearby anyway for these sort of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes. Yes. They just used to see us over the worst of it you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you both share the same set of friends or did you each have your own friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No, we - we had the same set.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Were friends ever invited into the home at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Would you have people in very often?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - fairly, you know, I was on pretty good terms with most of 'em and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Would this be for particular occasions they'd come in or just casual visits?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No. Just walk in if they happened to come by.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Would they stay for something to eat and drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well not very often, occasionally they would.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you ever go out visiting friends at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No, I wasn't much of a one to go out. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
People often tell us that in those days people made their own amusements, what did you used to do when you got together with your friends in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - really we didn't do much entertaining did we, you know. Yes, we just sit around
 the fire and talk farming or - any local interest you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Just a social chat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Yes. And they'd leave - they'd clear off about half past eight or nine. Those in the evening, well, sometime - wasn't very often me wife used to come up here, 'cos t
here was the three girls here, or two. There was always two and occasionally three, well - they were both interested - all interested in the chapel and in the temperance movement, and me wife was - used to play the organ - when she could and train the chi
ldren to sing. They used to have a - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3570294\charrsid11886030 eisteddfod}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
 - a competition like, singing competition and my sister and my wife used to do it you see. Me wife was a -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 She was a bit more musical?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes she was, there was - but that didn't come into the children
. I'm hoping that'll come into the next generation but I don't know whether it will.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 I expect it'll crop up sometime.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes, it will.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Who were considered as the most important people in the area at that time, about the 1918 period?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well
 - I expect - the most important person in the village - was - Mr Darton who was the - the magistrate. He was a magistrate and he was on the Rural District Council, and was Chairman of the - of the church council I believe and - he was on various public b
odies, and I expect most people would call him the most important man.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 He was a big local }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3570294\charrsid11886030 landowner}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030  was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No. No. He was a local farmer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 He was a bachelor wasn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 But he had an interest in the rural affairs didn't he, took an interest in the village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 He did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 So why would you say he was important, because of his activities rather than the amount of land he had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 No, that was because - him being - on the Council and being Chairman of it, you know, if you we
re Chairman of the School Board - or any odd thing then crops up, well - you - you go and have a chat with him you see. 'Cos he - he'd be the - if you wanted something done - well you'd see him first you see, and then decide whether to bring it up to the 
council or not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Who else would you say was important in the community?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Well you see - we weren't blessed - with a Squire. Or - and - and the Reverend Jones up here, well - I - suppose he was a - a little better off, but there was - this was sort 
of a democratic village. There wasn't any wealthy people. You know. Some had more than others of course, but - we never had a - a leading light. Like some villages. That - that didn't apply here much. Some villages I mean the Squire'd own very likely the 
whole of the Parish. And then everything turned - he was the hub of the village like he was. No one done anything unless they asked him. But that didn't apply here. One chap was as good as his master here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Would you say there was any distinction in the sort of person who went to the chapel and sort of person who went to the church here?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Well - but not much. There was a little difference - when there was an election on between the Conservatives and the Liberals, you know. The Liberals were mostly n
onconformist and the - and the Conservatives were - were mostly church people. Well - then sometimes relations were a bit strained for about a month or six weeks, but we soon got over it didn't we. They didn't let much get between them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 People would show their loyalties by suddenly deciding to go to church or chapel would they at election time?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Ah. Not exactly that, no, but - the - the - the children sometimes would start in the Sunday school, ooh, about three weeks before the treat. You know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
How about the working class strata of the village, did they all have roughly the same standard of living or were there some rather poorer ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - there's always a few shiftless people, who - under any circumstances will be - will you kn
ow, got no idea how to spend the money or - how to manage, but people who knew how to manage, they lived fairly well, and some of them even well. But of course a family made a difference, if you got three or four children to keep you see, they couldn't li
ve very high.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3570294\charrsid11886030 What were the farm labourers' wages about 1918 around here?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Well - you see - 1918 is just about the end of the war you see, and wages - wages got up to fifty-two and sixpence a week. That was the highest I paid, fifty-two and six. A
nd of course the time soon come - when we went back onto the gold standard, you see, then - prices fell so, and - well - I - got a man working for me, but - I told him, I said, well, I can't - keep you on at this wage, you see. I said, you'll have to get 
a
nother job. I said, I - I won't give you notice, but if you can get a job take it. Well guv'nor, he said, what'll you - what'll you reckon you'll do. You can't farm your farm yourself. I said, I shall have to do the best I can. But I can't pay you. Well f
ortunate enough - in a week he got a job up at Tiptree with a house attached to the job and he took it and he stayed there for the rest of his life. Yes. He - Sidney Blythe. He didn't make old bones, he died when he was about sixty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 How did this wage compare with say 1913 or before the war affected it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
Well, you see - about thirteen bob - in 1913. And fifty-two and sixpence at 1918, was four times as much. And my uncle said to me - when wages get over a pound a week I'm going to give up farming.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Who was that, Uncle William?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Did you have to struggle to make ends meet yourself up to 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Well - I - I never was very flush I can tell you that. 30 - in '34 - times changed - then - me family were all getting their own living. 
And they were no cost to me. They'd been a minimum cost before, mind you, but still they cost something. But they were earning their own living in 1934. And then prices got better.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15401715 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 For the farming?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13566012 OF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 Yes.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\ql \fi-461\li461\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid15401715 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3500228\charrsid11886030 
\par }}